mtr:GCST90200242_GCST90199839 a mtr:MetaboliteRatio ;
    rdfs:label "taurochenodeoxycholic acid 3-sulfate to taurocholenate sulfate*" ;
    mtr:has_denominator chebi:166739 ;
    mtr:llm_gene_phenotype_relationship " Reduced SLC10A2 function due to missense variants leads to decreased intestinal bile acid reabsorption, altering the bile acid pool and increasing the risk of cholelithiasis (gallstones).[1](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQHatgrKWtnStwi05cr-DQI39y7sgjKKb8r8ziPNXD7VxxSSjlvbGWAopO-Sa0c0VuVMIiZi0N-0bGPhsIGmEDx6yzvDE5pN1bWWma9vzhnUctrfq7Lfr9YFYBYN46bL1xN3DPGSJitZOY4BhxQ=), [11](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQFtZjJz511wLvYegSDzam0obStJTncCZpiCIy1F8YiHciAHQj1AdVXmYXegkoXq7kxdRFJlSnMtQLGwxzMYlTzdO0jIfTrRki8-vq2WS9QLkTQcTD-R_x4UXL4wVqYbeHcTwguyeae33sqbCTq_DQPDPb3JQdqf5f6uWHMrn-z4decjwbyFBG0t7vFfVLBmHDUHhkJWHpCav5luyZkWiDWTpgnWvLx154vi-4yyl4TH_cnRilm1x5Nkbs_5GGmcw6k1Ffq7yGDdilrZAWjNqDjAdo7BGAjXpSjdiw==), [12](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQEquDnASFQ6HOdQObDj9383pkKj75xFnBToCUDaDRb1FfWQRWUk_732bvrYplwGpGAtXcmzeocalqVhzMfcR4HzimpTK77IpHZzRHzPM-QBv0oV5w1XCg5SADsMK-_bHVDPjTw9VqQGJxVD7dfsKP-X_o61rNjGEKHc7s-cY3uQrW8NzlMxDslfeK_BAioW-umsNAIqMnyF8ZXt2ASRfdCGE8OFCnft_iCsXlV9ki96a-X7oGwyJEc4inbWLxsE6E65lOOC) This altered bile acid profile is reflected in the metabolite ratio. " ;
    mtr:llm_phenotype_driver " Gene-centric:SLC10A2" ;
    mtr:llm_ratio_evidence " metabolites not in a pathway but enzyme catalyzes one metabolite " ;
    mtr:llm_ratio_explanation " The ratio reflects bile acid metabolism and transport. Missense variants in the SLC10A2 gene can impair the reabsorption of bile acids, including these sulfated forms. " ;
    mtr:max_pgain "3.181818345155765e+18"^^xsd:float .

