mtr:GCST90199798_GCST90199675 a mtr:MetaboliteRatio ;
    rdfs:label "isobutyrylglycine to homoarginine" ;
    mtr:has_denominator chebi:27747 ;
    mtr:has_numerator chebi:70979 ;
    mtr:llm_gene_phenotype_relationship " CPS1 missense variant likely impairs the urea cycle, leading to reduced homoarginine synthesis and contributing to hyperammonemia-related phenotypes like renal failure and cholelithiasis.[1](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQFw7zPHFgkoiOMtes4lIGVhT9ifxZbmA1TG_07AIIrfa6WqFm5c8QP6XKesT-ovQKguzoMYI9LS5h8wJFDfm_wbt7tLzXYHNzH3uJCzmAqNXO1dLF3hB2plea610nEOQ1vEzuvJ), [2](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQGXFQceVZtWO4szNuSOrBTRX86MX7_rer9oTIcUJ1UjKWphzxA7-N4n41Wte5KAdxpjhJIwNoi_BkZo3kvM8SbRdNCc85YdhnzxEjNPxAV-oGirVSMK4VjnN_DN9osyiZYn0_DkiQk=), [9](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQHXcCaJJjPLs6rC8Vxtz0UUM-7IS_j6tVmD2ZYQELcoKuSv17RoFtFmnMCOQjwsFR9zJ0G3bFu-LN4SBJHdufMdPAtglyUg0ELgmqgwdmQIXLmyf3e0yo3Dp_67PAm4cJDNtvMCcsN4om58ho3IyoKWNj7J_Ys=), [10](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQGRIhCsM0HSWA6NVvh7FVOG7PRSaAuyl17d-y7NU9xPQuSnObhxSGCDW-ugT5kn5-Y-uClPWToyPWSO4VqelNFG751jFd_InZ50JbILmfqdwLNiCHZl59E4o-_bAawmn5jKFy6B) The accumulation of isobutyrylglycine may indicate secondary effects on branched-chain amino acid metabolism.[4](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQGqDvgP0R0_kyfAAk0JYpUvHN4TLevUsjAPiA0yzk4yUCqPA7Z677XPuSBSx-coCTjY6QqSpmPSnzApePrPOCRqZ_dwYjHvBto-Izfdv9DtsU-_q-gq-3eI-qodQ5G-FHBhgMPr) " ;
    mtr:llm_phenotype_driver " Gene-centric:CPS1" ;
    mtr:llm_ratio_evidence " metabolites not in a pathway but enzyme catalyzes one metabolite " ;
    mtr:llm_ratio_explanation " This ratio may reflect a shift in nitrogen metabolism, where decreased urea cycle function (homoarginine) could coincide with altered branched-chain amino acid breakdown (isobutyrylglycine). " ;
    mtr:max_pgain "1.023998105599646e+25"^^xsd:float .

mtr:GCST90199945_GCST90200134 a mtr:MetaboliteRatio ;
    rdfs:label "sphingomyelin (d18:1/14:0, d16:1/16:0)* to sphingomyelin (d18:1/25:0, d19:0/24:1, d20:1/23:0, d19:1/24:0)*" ;
    mtr:has_numerator chebi:64486 ;
    mtr:llm_gene_phenotype_relationship " Altered SGPP1 function likely dysregulates the balance of sphingomyelin species. This can impact lipoprotein metabolism, platelet function, and insulin signaling, leading to lipidaemias, and changes in platelet count, HbA1c, and triglycerides.[6](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQFrWoSQRnvQwLMaggtQtFiM5eT08rlAwqjZjE4viRBnlrdsTaIu5MFtlK2iW-8r_NIUhW47bp9R5IMnUtdafg3sWdOMzDLiD99wO4lDm1p_5qo8r-Oeyd3HgKmVHC9C9P8ZxCFNJvx-G6eYv90Cu63uErNDSthGj01-uFHuLVVRf1JQb9BETJAHy-iZvJXz5DXoVqrREWMRX0wUG1zAaChw2xYKzVLricc=), [7](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQF8-9-yalmTmLUR0d1iqTYNyI6aqrhUi28Je1odZs7MKCrRCsZRYtaWv7641ZVjsJxBxIPfeqPyB5qfqRA08cJwNTvU3zFv_DXCty4pBb6MhnlbWDQ8Oagr5bd9VDL-jnVdeI1Xjp28YT22JaCNUulclfkf), [8](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQFDkzYF3KN_yY47o4VCvJp8JHTytwrEYUA_k77V5Po18622KLU1Fgna5uCuRrXvtpYvzpcfMWbVgd9EKWdlv0RCMLn5n-q30wjObLwp5eWo1Y9yzk4rtBWSm3xIHJHPyyXvPxRbmWN5qI8eua38TCV173A6aN1yTST0kgOQ80dTFtQfiesF1JCQ8-R8REhoY3OvClEc), [9](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQEkhbbiEqImp2RmMtjMjeVkje-CrXzAKFQdKRrVJgZ2oVZ-JGMnsfKoL6f_3XA0sx0bYxr8xRp3xLmSjuWYb8wd5am0o5zT7vgKCdrcniVW12TZs__QzI2tf5IbXZF5Ba1aPUFrOw==) " ;
    mtr:llm_phenotype_driver " Gene-centric:SGPP1" ;
    mtr:llm_ratio_evidence " reaction where the ratio is shared through a pathway " ;
    mtr:llm_ratio_explanation " The ratio reflects the balance between shorter-chain (numerator) and very-long-chain (denominator) sphingomyelins, potentially modulated by SGPP1's role in supplying precursors for ceramide synthesis.[1](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQE2dJCbMfxHR6IN_nHHmgK1Tl7ydslEEXIuqx9-ZXCkDsp4b3maYbtzT3ZNeuzDfQBDlm9tdXeX8Kl4KkuVRZiKKhRHGBNKfcXJfM8Za49X8Xy_oDURPB5YH-EjFMnGQvmXQlTgCPLdpcw=), [5](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQGH-GJTgpR6S5lt20RPi_jItJKR4M7byAlICiUNPqwNvY46O1O4-qWW777xBlklrHAwkoSO4AHfa1JgvVfFczmgoAnnGEOkmcqhW0IHXTrpBPoXOy4JbWZe8Qd3wHHufCAzKw==) " ;
    mtr:max_pgain "8.758865197285172e+32"^^xsd:float .

mtr:GCST90200359_GCST90200366 a mtr:MetaboliteRatio ;
    rdfs:label "5-methylthioadenosine (mta) to creatinine" ;
    mtr:has_denominator chebi:16737 ;
    mtr:has_numerator chebi:17509 ;
    mtr:llm_gene_phenotype_relationship " Reduced CPS1 function, indicated by the missense variant, is linked to chronic kidney disease and cholelithiasis, potentially through impaired nitrogen metabolism and altered bile composition, respectively.[15](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQGL9qeO2tTFZhfId7pIEldHtbhC2tbDoScPNQ1jon7ky_KRJFd67mKmnRMhth-fZr_iKbHSvZqlS2UR_x1rCpwUpg3Y9uB-roY2WKDrb1dMbnoBxBiqfRkdflF8CRE-mHE=), [16](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQHmy2V45bbNd4i5lqwFciq43YU8fjirYuD7qv95zlZcaUUc9ZP-ALpymCHG_CUfgEVDu_DrXvcZtkB_UBkGGeGLiQNitlfctNCMsEKP_d5I9S89AscvnpK_RRgAfJIzC1WtE0amkgtYH-Yaiwc=), [17](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQHpQJkeTpRb6eeGm8UGR6uHYM-toF1Qf2q9XRBrLpmLkGSzVsV1xKz9GVI7qX9XoFB9AGcWaEiYdASI_DM7xPzTB4kbx9TfzGz4T8YTDk5Xk8wHBF-xslZJDHpARUfhTKcOdVlg) " ;
    mtr:llm_phenotype_driver " Gene-centric:CPS1" ;
    mtr:llm_ratio_evidence " metabolites unrelated " ;
    mtr:llm_ratio_explanation " CPS1 dysfunction impacts nitrogen disposal via the urea cycle, while creatinine reflects muscle mass and kidney function; their direct biochemical link is not established. " ;
    mtr:max_pgain "12682428.62111926"^^xsd:float ;
    mtr:reaction_distance 5 .

