    mtr:llm_ratio_explanation " This ratio of docosapentaenoate (22:5n3) to its downstream product nisinate (24:6n3) reflects the efficiency of the omega-3 fatty acid elongation and desaturation pathway influenced by ELOVL2.[3](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQHO8AjJVm1jQ-PLxPZMHZ_q2R23kpWtmcYrxVVN8HCQav5y2Uy_OiONPrOM9a6RzXBm5ZtSOaaKYaGhC1yIa4qT5ALXgCKZolmrskDn7AUotC-58Ac9F5bfHOMYvXVNN1_21SyPyu3ibOZRrg==), [9](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQHnlSvbbogRB0myt9mwoh_vrCEfGMhO0USrwc0amSA-gI1516sKFwnC_jLSVrS51-TZYrBNH8EhScX1mNQa1i138YgDfc6sjrxK_mTxweuUSII4pfWFu0Kw0AQ-Bmwyud0RutIoc98RMh0upqDQqquOMFODEm6j4xY5GOzw-4w91SDCHf6Bodk6QU6PPOGT9KKIC_1e1bkA) " ;
    mtr:max_pgain "41141734828212.84"^^xsd:float .

mtr:GCST90199846_GCST90200119 a mtr:MetaboliteRatio ;
    rdfs:label "glycosyl-n-stearoyl-sphingosine (d18:1/18:0) to glycosyl ceramide (d18:1/23:1, d17:1/24:1)*" ;
    mtr:llm_gene_phenotype_relationship " Altered CERS4 function, suggested by the eQTL, likely shifts ceramide profiles, a mechanism linked to inflammation in gout and noted in polyneuropathies.[3](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQGOzRk4Sfr5CBHIzNENGUoq4Nk4RdRdmC2TQRg6-6aBhtF5977OuOdOrB63qcxGU1StqX26JA4QTFjxYIU6Uvcb_VGc7T6AEaZwEyBM9wQ0oxKZdnev-ySjfoK_qM28dlAOa4YJc-cyFv8QTJP7Y5Q51W_EqPWFzUHn0zytbmKTdV5el6D88XZpG8-oB-VoOHb-ympCGryC-GEDOrYyRYc94aRxU9ADpUV6_UFJsAqnkYZ-erlHI9aFeNUQEbNbMt3aiKPvss8=), [4](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQFEMJEqlU8A9yPQf76EEM8o7HyaR0VVDt6EMXAdFrKdX0qfrY9UufyCCRPmlzjc7TwPVXcnVwwqN52llWn_uQWS6mNRKaIFA6LatLrNYHfonrTIPIvCqI-OK8Ig2uWeR-qOfK4UqcMMFKqRoQ7MR_1FdgiC7qZp), [5](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQFlDi2jagIas3iMbTSCPN0SELobdPg4HlMIIDGauOepAxmPwww7qfyQ59UvZUQtPQ0uHR_3ZgIZCvbyazrIejOT__K2ahgiDbrSerNWkmMmYKq4cq8JfHmpWgJjEKhpgswMKmEhTw==), [6](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQFtI56zfu73HwUFj7YOFUztUjfNO_oAlGQ1s2d8yr21eE1xR4QJBHWfEqgPpRHp5SVF120Q0_YtpiaOjbwCrShYAhzQ_vjLPlASvTKirMyojJmEhZDi8L4FsGQzb9L8dODLiMkzKM--OijhFpE=) " ;
    mtr:llm_phenotype_driver " Gene-centric:CERS4" ;
    mtr:llm_ratio_evidence " metabolites not in a pathway but enzyme catalyzes one metabolite " ;
    mtr:llm_ratio_explanation " The ratio reflects CERS4 activity, comparing the abundance of a C18:0 ceramide product with very-long-chain species, indicating a shift in ceramide composition. " ;
    mtr:max_pgain "23380869.2558667"^^xsd:float .

