mtr:GCST90200335_GCST90200448 a mtr:MetaboliteRatio ;
    rdfs:label "stearoyl sphingomyelin (d18:1/18:0) to n-stearoyl-sphinganine (d18:0/18:0)*" ;
    mtr:has_denominator chebi:67033 ;
    mtr:has_numerator chebi:83358 ;
    mtr:llm_gene_phenotype_relationship " HNF1A likely regulates genes in sphingolipid synthesis; altered activity, reflected by the ratio, may impact hepatic lipid and cholesterol metabolism, contributing to the increased risk of cholelithiasis and cardiovascular disease.[1](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQHa9GzVFxUwf_EcMpXmyfHmgUk8OVLbGBy8eLYORt0lyaUEZAv-PVS4FGAJxKdr7Bt_E9pkgC-AwNBp29eZ2XQ1LvO-v_kua0BGDU7367dnVJ6dDES3q6qyf21KY9cLC5Vyy_-uq9_88NiDoHs=), [11](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQF_kYtzZs1k3mo7gP4oOuory0kacFmUeLZhVcwiJRmMa6EWJp7HCyFmJGyeCcd0_-oBzO6RVXJNYrTnb6Z0V3CAmIe1dzFZdvoUjLUH9qiM2rx7yXCn8_hPukPuDWDbXMLexg==), [12](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQHacR-i-_jV_kqWnh7yIvl0ctSbcvG6yKhGNTH9WirX6WXBPLq036eXiDjVjW55sRdEo3nGglpR2WUS1Tt_sK3J32T3O5jSJ9q6fCdpwgIW9fNsR7UeIGX0RBslVnzvVXL1DfHki9jiUCKiiV4=), [13](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQGDFpXAqH6RISCA6skwhHmwbKHvWKNgmUHuQl8MEHthJYJs1ZxzQEBHrHGBFw02u0psZ-mlBN1pp1oCjgjMkdgjVs1cZSkan4ZzAx1L6H9mVjp8E3drc1ruFonmYbx_O_mlvCoX) " ;
    mtr:llm_phenotype_driver " Gene-centric:[HNF1A]" ;
    mtr:llm_ratio_evidence " reaction where the ratio is shared through a pathway " ;
    mtr:llm_ratio_explanation " This ratio reflects the conversion of n-stearoyl-sphinganine (a dihydroceramide) to stearoyl sphingomyelin, a key maturation step in the de novo sphingolipid synthesis pathway.[9](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQHrL_vC3VE3_rkRo4TL9vjN9svhj_Ig8mSVcOEuZLL3V1EhB-ywDUKoh1BquuCiVz6IcEX_Ll5bKPFZJ-qUmDzC2LIaeMtESNjDx7JMUAmk7HNmK4ZDYmom-S-c429-5YeKoNRcnpqb00awSGo=), [10](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQHOC4u6rUdLE7JfMcaCxIqTBBzd31yN5UbWwuW_iIZoQeQ4m9UegMvy1ZSBl4ZeAZmtg496kY_QdPlkrcY2d64Nl25TASwd2LamsfxURULKy0RteTxTW6nHZNzIznvViFwksrLeYIKeB198x61e), [6](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQHcX6pzF9NHb6NxDH9M8GB1TS7TIvt4oyjlngXVlayniGbt23Cxunllsm7h2ba6q1snFS88bBl3RSyM_WMuuvV2cfjQyxcfxopowy7b1Zxvk8C5HJ4EVrHTREB6w0m2eKWgn33jlQ==) " ;
    mtr:max_pgain "35202092.00744175"^^xsd:float .

mtr:GCST90200341_GCST90200448 a mtr:MetaboliteRatio ;
    rdfs:label "n-stearoyl-sphingosine (d18:1/18:0)* to n-stearoyl-sphinganine (d18:0/18:0)*" ;
    mtr:has_denominator chebi:67033 ;
    mtr:has_numerator chebi:72961 ;
    mtr:llm_gene_phenotype_relationship " HNF1A variants are associated with cholelithiasis.[5](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQEm-SkBPQww0BtJbsLHiw60ZWe_UePqggwK0rk7iZRNJ2hECiWKRmvTRmzckbPAhVKmHwlzC4HyMIqhCTIDgxDaJhttfjNBQNeJ5RSgZ4b9c3iC_i2V4diT5OKTc9GDiVY3), [12](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQFP_vJVszBxes4eucdRxkohKnJKuX8zcQ7HEsq8eijAGeMtUGx68__FVN6IVTCjKOABIqrtZFP8t1m0HA5JhkRMp9zQvN7r1WHaa-LR4ollIRyS8i9hlaHJqzwh3-IiNwowv4zjot8Bw22fDznE6a819vHf-ePZOl8QsaHBTbsFpEHDwDmj8Z-CLk2lU9NWcwPyGA==), [13](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQEGXhbQl5psYVtRDlrsO2VujARMOUrP8jZKcyEts5gmj6bltJ_xddzXRj4kRvcZgtRH27EmQe-YwewKuT8feSBX6zYs1y21ce693ajehGcfTEKcXHr5Mh86EsQ=) HNF1A regulates sphingolipid metabolism genes.[4](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQGkckZs0kZJL1qnDWUmL1cTSn8cqQtQPD9hQYbF4lviJU_9Q9OgXWxJzmC-c1J0Ry527DKosxkXgIO7Uza3S2OghvBFTX-anoPbV7yfvj6yxyEALLr_XQvcfKGuyh4AAYOevj8=) Altered sphingolipid metabolism, reflected by the ratio, could contribute to gallstone formation, potentially through effects on cholesterol and bile acid regulation.[5](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQEm-SkBPQww0BtJbsLHiw60ZWe_UePqggwK0rk7iZRNJ2hECiWKRmvTRmzckbPAhVKmHwlzC4HyMIqhCTIDgxDaJhttfjNBQNeJ5RSgZ4b9c3iC_i2V4diT5OKTc9GDiVY3), [14](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQFL3zz1aiVmnsyD_otdxlZGzqN8rQ_PEeazJNd3XL1pcOLjrna8gNpnNdmMGzg1QV9T48m74BjOzEuJv_dp5qbumMe7NF4OVszgx409sZWAH6ZmR_AvonfnDpMZFt_IM7_4TqRzfBchS8Sw6Q==) " ;
    mtr:llm_phenotype_driver " Gene-centric:HNF1A" ;
    mtr:llm_ratio_evidence " metabolites not in a pathway but enzyme catalyzes one metabolite " ;
    mtr:llm_ratio_explanation " This ratio reflects the activity of a desaturase enzyme in the ceramide synthesis pathway, converting the denominator (saturated) to the numerator (monounsaturated). " ;
    mtr:max_pgain "48691948105090.32"^^xsd:float .

