    mtr:llm_gene_phenotype_relationship " Reduced SLC22A5 function impairs carnitine uptake, hindering palmitoylcarnitine formation and mitochondrial fatty acid oxidation.[1](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQHwowo9MxH3bw67bN3_EYmiiKbAtekkHru9r5uP810zy-B1FXlk4w2ZyoQF_Ny1PQL5wL5bBzNPjjxEUI14baLqfZu0bqVpFVhvfo9ZtvGP6HqO33c3cFp_PlE8izK2hQ==), [2](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQGf9tHTfcIw4LYqwyB-b0UimmTjNLvb859B2MosOJXuzoKuS597BTbfqFWtCP8RPg0XCBdAhTodUekUewi-4o4U192rCy44kLJqdD119ICyBgOmXnmnzKM-gGiLSbOMcoquijnB5Ce3jsFQNV_xWiaK2v1upg==), [3](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQGUccDnwLkNUfRUDBYIhYFeUlaLQoVTol13mqSmBIFJIy_aDRZDvdyiusBMRGnxYaRWoExwtHWjiF1nUA27ivUq6uM8n-kPqUVqBhH04cxy_HyBNM6z_UGZrYb32Yg0SW1ch68eESYmmA==) This can lead to myocardial lipid accumulation and energy deficiency, increasing the risk of myocardial infarction and ischemic heart disease.[11](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQGnffNHVuHwSeddA5jqo4Vnvc3k_m3cdl-mBFVH1hyliSr-9Aet7or_F9J-QXVdfSVtyLsWL11ievyRQEbzLEK_X9IWN9i8jYWmFgIhFM-gOqP7r4PNg24KyJ7On_RFv5FCjw7B7xMSwwYQSKzZ1BK0zPrlfzmVj1LhZernBmmwuXaBjHvMnycuIXnJgVZ1LZKmLgl5_IbaMwWQJaH1dzMPVnU=), [12](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQGh5oDmQjOugZpKsnyf2gzNTifBTdTiUTIhg9bdFbuQe06WGgQ2vbVsjdrdVCH37h4t_64eulY_sfTwG02OJZFce7deiz8vtrUMf8_00pk9CdMa8_I24cIesZy30SI7WhEXsER3mWGnXGxjfVoHOn3pR65-QShih2TwzWcgeDzqO8zTMQ==), [13](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQH5VH7pFCY98NSwmfBjU90ZFc_Auz5EIaX_h76fopLWB35a4XdJQFFfKbl8LOxTaS9F6nUPSyor9N_ZeqR-0OZp8v9Hs0YMkWLkvOfBjrFFIWMVt7-VEnRHAJINahHeQG6q3DLD7seRwAfwtWYgKsoQPT8=), [14](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQFqBAcT5fp4UY24McN83moQZ-nX1tjzWGcDVp1FKKgWMbIchYlqWu9V19JJQU8YPZNRhyheDQs1OCDjysrooPEJodjjDDJYLCV6R2A22z6r2ina582xrgGXShxTeSVROFgAoQeTv1GdFJKE8SdzQJw-_2CRSoIEEUggwLyZJLNLqgTsDpwjsBpHZnRmrdMIMbVxPZZLjJntLg==) " ;
    mtr:llm_phenotype_driver " Gene-centric:SLC22A5" ;
    mtr:llm_ratio_evidence " metabolites related through biology " ;
    mtr:llm_ratio_explanation " An elevated ratio suggests decreased carnitine-dependent fatty acid import and oxidation (denominator) relative to fatty acid synthesis (numerator), potentially due to impaired SLC22A5 function.[1](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQHwowo9MxH3bw67bN3_EYmiiKbAtekkHru9r5uP810zy-B1FXlk4w2ZyoQF_Ny1PQL5wL5bBzNPjjxEUI14baLqfZu0bqVpFVhvfo9ZtvGP6HqO33c3cFp_PlE8izK2hQ==), [2](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQGf9tHTfcIw4LYqwyB-b0UimmTjNLvb859B2MosOJXuzoKuS597BTbfqFWtCP8RPg0XCBdAhTodUekUewi-4o4U192rCy44kLJqdD119ICyBgOmXnmnzKM-gGiLSbOMcoquijnB5Ce3jsFQNV_xWiaK2v1upg==), [5](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQGoNuKbtNfT9-RE7SW88VTLNK5xP3Ygqx5FEeHa-afukfTzjLWV5Dll0tLxuoGB6pXLEeYg_PMRlo8QcMgiIwPXG3Degjwt5jodIU-foqDNE-Fl-dDXBJ9AGwOD3VXQl8xpxJYX25Wm5g==), [10](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQF8CExLGsT9a6Tg45JMDJHQQRvvzcJZwxWAQhYDtAdpweOOpxDK2RbhjN2w23epbkykNJSIIsP37YOw7hzQew67tqb7rOdZtSY5av4cSesNYMKssWtflNrRIoj4G50UNmC4cSEpHqy-fyWU) " ;
