mtr:GCST90199854_GCST90199855 a mtr:MetaboliteRatio ;
    rdfs:label "5alpha-pregnan-3beta,20alpha-diol monosulfate (2) to 5alpha-androstan-3beta,17beta-diol monosulfate (2)" ;
    mtr:llm_gene_phenotype_relationship " Genetic variants in SULT2A1 alter its enzymatic activity, affecting the balance of sulfated steroids and bile acids, which is a known risk factor for cholelithiasis (gallstone disease).[8](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQHsbXraUbHNYJYjs0-Pke3q5C4Kjzbmdc7HHaeWZv-A3g7SW9K7UUFHBAtihh1IIoK0M51vdiVQQ7ovULLQGm8FZEMpsXFiaJ7gHGFx84lDjoQ5F98R8VIUUgXM2Pr0E_tyY9maTsDE_BCTUwM=), [9](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQFT2bZr29M_9FCFWryFFO-4Xrj8NuwrJfcRJg3lj1Ofynwhcw4SEFR3APGVw2fnH-c4EyZQpU56wbxiDqNZiznH2us_MXkZAOdwGe0C0w9ImZNpAtuoiQu4KaqQEhH0wl9Kl7h0aZikKWUYqNfC), [10](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQGOWTm8ApGTM4hr3QHCCKGhtazY8QRAYTsNTQQrE4ZovDIWCZIrdI2PAWin24xNpUSDGMN6WBvbhBefKalfIU1LvZSiXtt-HaS3VtxpN7-VZR3OigbsWE0kjmpLm2SlfFDhmZaL5KbwPayo6QJMuUthhatCN9VQn1-1XXDU6k5MT6XzswR1EgfYg8EpLCV6MVneMNS6g0dC4sUfbKTDjtbiHY435RTI7BiwDcb03TEDk1cDuBMtcKu9t8mq1rqnDg==) " ;
    mtr:llm_phenotype_driver " Gene-centric:SULT2A1" ;
    mtr:llm_ratio_evidence " metabolites related through biology " ;
    mtr:llm_ratio_explanation " The ratio reflects the relative activity of SULT2A1 on pregnane and androstane steroid precursors, indicating a preference or efficiency of sulfation between these two steroid classes. " ;
    mtr:max_pgain "35551077.84346677"^^xsd:float .

mtr:GCST90199854_GCST90199856 a mtr:MetaboliteRatio ;
    rdfs:label "5alpha-pregnan-3beta,20alpha-diol monosulfate (2) to androstenediol (3alpha, 17alpha) monosulfate (3)" ;
    mtr:llm_gene_phenotype_relationship " Genetic variants in SULT2A1 alter the sulfation of steroids and bile acids, and this dysregulation is associated with cholelithiasis.[3](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQFijEKx74_1wx74F4kVrqDk6c6u8mgW2n7kpVbtF9y4sCp7mTnlvCZsE1lLD6OvEa3RJs-YUGaL94IgxqcjicKE18WPZJopCxYqMZWLAHwCoSvFGZzPQPTQspNNtU01Udy_6CaHwl6xSxx45enOLnheXfe04Q==), [4](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQGDyTXTh-Ls1lERc1C-vwQmkEeU58dUFUoqB6VseoTn8vGQzIRNmVU_flLj3h9NYXsGaZ4stsm0UCS-WXejGt2WyCxLrE-7fK1t1HSqEY4PHEa1ULrOan6Wqy_ZpySQWZ4kHjZxFtsKTjXV9-M=), [5](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQEsXbHYhdqxgf0UQ_UgNCjoSlApy-2aLy1_8ZLvQ24BUZtL-yqO0T4DzSI0jjbSpd6aopdmLtRQKQ7tYSU8Fb2FlQH_5oxFuXd2XW7VxbeicdLH-APqRKJaMq5TQdqkmQFGbCCAeQ69X1aO2qs=) The ratio serves as a biomarker for SULT2A1 activity, linking the gene to the phenotype of gallstone disease.[4](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQGDyTXTh-Ls1lERc1C-vwQmkEeU58dUFUoqB6VseoTn8vGQzIRNmVU_flLj3h9NYXsGaZ4stsm0UCS-WXejGt2WyCxLrE-7fK1t1HSqEY4PHEa1ULrOan6Wqy_ZpySQWZ4kHjZxFtsKTjXV9-M=), [6](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQG2kkqy9M-Yaoq04RtuyX_BR7fddD0sft67In8XUfpihNIlRJnsK_ADxh14TvNwNT0ziVFS9ZoQe9MFmi1Cv3OwHTgkDwnXaHqV0F_gWZGYE-X6yEMp3bqPJC3wgiy8FzAl_tuB4W7m-sTyOU61FwRzjfm2tcl4JppfUsDLWG_5--Fkjl1Hahcqact3MgEF9_ANXh15-Q2Hr6TBZ5i0EcSH6pUrOZTW1W6w-fI6fPlnHHadZLAS1CBD7UCaLCgLk5j-pM6vfw==) " ;
    mtr:llm_phenotype_driver " Gene-centric:SULT2A1" ;
    mtr:llm_ratio_evidence " metabolites related through biology " ;
    mtr:llm_ratio_explanation " The ratio reflects SULT2A1's relative activity on pregnane versus androstane steroids, indicating its metabolic preference and overall function in steroid hormone processing. " ;
    mtr:max_pgain "8.785124143715393e+35"^^xsd:float .

mtr:GCST90199917_GCST90200674 a mtr:MetaboliteRatio ;
    rdfs:label "pregnanediol-3-glucuronide to androsterone sulfate" ;
    mtr:has_denominator chebi:83037 ;
    mtr:llm_gene_phenotype_relationship " Genetic variants in SULT2A1 are associated with cholelithiasis.[8](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQHgEGqwnKHkmDxSsxA5VlebVjGtIspUaiRBfeF257ooGHSwtgFDdW10Su1ytyQpNzUsTigeJX2spJ2G4u9ec7t5o5RIxAZ4j0bTzhqyWc_rLhJ0EoageSlMuWEj_kKlsNXaH7KIJjJHMFCT7-txfXS2H16GzLornoZla2TXjAsMC3Cof1zl), [9](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQE6hiaLRvddfET9-MAgziXB-V4hyY0kGB65fJzPVi9EqZAr7n_sABcJQibi5Fsr4-_pTj2Dc61tU3ONcQJ-MypK14ciCBoqv9d9sIsBlgHcLsNe9_BzgsAmAszl-o_HsIfWFTaMT79wPBnmJ64=) SULT2A1's role in steroid and bile acid sulfation is a plausible mechanism; altered sulfation could disrupt bile composition, leading to gallstone formation.[1](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQGkeHei6_TcvBdUUEoGju0AdAxIfG2Ik3He5ne_EkiTferQwt_DzDYhXNYTeomo2jOVwRGB-U0xHslnCvHSRIiMvLCYRdeuMAcKjZA9ACiuzaXU7P4pS3luj-25GQ9RdMTHxBZg57hbU4-S1pnv7IJ1xTmDMNU=), [8](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQHgEGqwnKHkmDxSsxA5VlebVjGtIspUaiRBfeF257ooGHSwtgFDdW10Su1ytyQpNzUsTigeJX2spJ2G4u9ec7t5o5RIxAZ4j0bTzhqyWc_rLhJ0EoageSlMuWEj_kKlsNXaH7KIJjJHMFCT7-txfXS2H16GzLornoZla2TXjAsMC3Cof1zl), [9](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQE6hiaLRvddfET9-MAgziXB-V4hyY0kGB65fJzPVi9EqZAr7n_sABcJQibi5Fsr4-_pTj2Dc61tU3ONcQJ-MypK14ciCBoqv9d9sIsBlgHcLsNe9_BzgsAmAszl-o_HsIfWFTaMT79wPBnmJ64=) " ;
    mtr:llm_phenotype_driver " Gene-centric:SULT2A1" ;
    mtr:llm_ratio_evidence " metabolites not in a pathway but enzyme catalyzes one metabolite " ;
    mtr:llm_ratio_explanation " The ratio reflects the balance between progesterone and androgen metabolic pathways, where SULT2A1-mediated sulfation influences the clearance of androsterone.[1](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQGkeHei6_TcvBdUUEoGju0AdAxIfG2Ik3He5ne_EkiTferQwt_DzDYhXNYTeomo2jOVwRGB-U0xHslnCvHSRIiMvLCYRdeuMAcKjZA9ACiuzaXU7P4pS3luj-25GQ9RdMTHxBZg57hbU4-S1pnv7IJ1xTmDMNU=), [5](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQGg81_qLMDEM1YuwH01aTJJQXgtKSaxVgAkMxJdJucqBlL-nfXgmeXwvBT_IkKfgJzQxtXo6dj30o0V33RRBTbIJ4MnU2aZ1T_NuohzKSXUobXCsFPxBXFvyB_qiPNRNAHSTEKzfcqFXZ0lxn0wxt96hrxGcOM9CLTA_egSsQS9cCa88CQjiSaTl0GAevI9BF9PAQ0G), [3](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQHQcjjsQt0WKtHQAOXYWgvLNmnnEGo2egx45A5s0ds17zPLoDacR0NLOpnUxl4Ap1rKRU0OopMOVsNlPoHQhUmPXZb5xtID7pksheDvuBAf_nN5m_N_1nYE-dU0T0AX61SCTPtP00K02ZS_MfXo0KVLHPOevlsqFdEAUY8=), [6](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQE-GQmeEYVXIvsCKh9Xc7766gA9oT2l8enGiuhOpMMmWQRuwyBt6KRveU9BZqsjnMdvtHKAbqY-5mknJri7_mmz2SrmQX2HDsqitUOCAhaMbT_BoCJ3t8sU33Kv-ASW4ozK862u-f2cQBXaButqNrv1IG_Qf5Mxhgbk1QJdT6tCz3kOoKw=), [7](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQHMLdl6zItWvyvv9YqFbFQshPqMz-VajTTDuv1NtZzk9ELJkAe7AN2ffHbTrIEfsmxJd2x5Av2nyAYNPR7imcLvrMoaNPBJP_WuGPnVfbp6Ii8CN7LaRSAL3z48T0WC_720tcdznQ==) " ;
    mtr:max_pgain "6755162058.036365"^^xsd:float .

mtr:GCST90199975_GCST90200169 a mtr:MetaboliteRatio ;
    rdfs:label "sphingomyelin (d18:2/14:0, d18:1/14:1)* to sphingomyelin (d17:1/14:0, d16:1/15:0)*" ;
    mtr:llm_gene_phenotype_relationship " FADS1 gene variants impact the composition of fatty acids in sphingolipids and other lipids, which is associated with metabolic phenotypes like Type 2 diabetes, hypercholesterolemia, and cholelithiasis.[7](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQEJENqQQTwuS4rG4MPI_4Q9wVIeVRZ4rtuo716JH7tYSH8xT2WbAKQA92KtFO9OPKYGgCF2FTw5TGehUKqJ8-vSLL4qqtkqtoOTQiR3q8yyp1uAm-uSZSE0-N2nnlME6jnmJA==), [1](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQG7w6_UWyAVZRysEFcDZ35aloAg2I7arwqunwV1tbyJYL-y5HJ_eNCYPJqe3g6H4ffJNK3I8V2mAaoUJtvi4zBzxV6aJArbwi5lnLDn_7YGRcOPjnjS7yziuSOqX7Vj20MvHIGZvszaxKMKApq33UGYc35hVPA=), [8](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQGWsVLZRmNDu3yCY67ta5FMenWfb3_NFaOw28FbmrbrMqHgKNPD11Rr8pFXrp8bTPpxCv_ZOgi0TxApyPdtMXUILMPYF0XvsFPquuGMfm1RSgZaL3cx1Hos29-4R-ouC3eIp889UljnmqYsFAeBqU2jrMy76yC18tuVC8IqtCdc9AuA8ULngUXwpgJpvbly9Raoeb-7_PNAB3SttoM_mdK5a1trklgXdZ-RqkwL1F7tB-qM8fdGq5XrVHDVGd9z-g==) " ;
    mtr:llm_phenotype_driver " Gene-centric:FADS1" ;
    mtr:llm_ratio_evidence " metabolites not in a pathway but enzyme catalyzes one metabolite " ;
    mtr:llm_ratio_explanation " The ratio reflects the activity of fatty acid desaturase enzymes, like FADS1, which alter the saturation of fatty acid chains incorporated into sphingomyelins. " ;
    mtr:max_pgain "1.166528408639626e+17"^^xsd:float .

