mtr:GCST90200146_GCST90199651 a mtr:MetaboliteRatio ;
    rdfs:label "docosahexaenoylcarnitine (c22:6)* to Docosahexaenoate DHA; 22:6n3" ;
    mtr:has_denominator chebi:28125 ;
    mtr:llm_gene_phenotype_relationship " Reduced SLC22A5 function can impair fatty acid oxidation, the primary energy source for immune cells. This impairment likely alters the proliferation and maintenance of hematopoietic cell lineages, leading to the observed associations with monocyte, lymphocyte, and white blood cell counts.[7](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQEHSK9RhV6TEqjgI1yW7OQasg_CULpKsG22D7lVee5gS8eUK0K4hUL8TpteUYfPEzHrG4_Ujk1QwgnPZvvGn5wB4OblxED2vjW0LEJkNSEUuy5vkE6jg5w1EA5eDKUikXTd8M3ewtncDDXPSQ==), [8](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQEZQgFEb89w8bSq77jobHrhv86IzduvTbdoIMxmiW9y-WpaaTJjv0j-sFhm0kgJx9l5euV7LXnURJP8yBPvVGOlQVGLlHrov9QuPQGnr9r9ny3eeFfSWjCvMbdGuclQzwKGvQ==), [9](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQE5Njvv2-F3ZRKZ6b-NbcyZp3h8kXyLNl359sZYjUUvrsWqhOe72UPjtAeSOh6GxNN03JezOJ5yZ7xK1OojYBKDCYl62KyqGF3qn-O3ITRZvFEZxFo1JBMd5WSiwOWgH_sLS3T6FifksY_uYbUPYT6Sk7NWGR9i69Zz6UOST5_nXUAjQg==) " ;
    mtr:llm_phenotype_driver " Gene-centric:SLC22A5" ;
    mtr:llm_ratio_evidence " metabolites related through biology " ;
    mtr:llm_ratio_explanation " The ratio reflects the carnitine-dependent conversion of DHA to its acylcarnitine for mitochondrial transport, a process reliant on the SLC22A5 carnitine transporter.[1](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQGSKUV0HoXQagIq_3gukReIbycGkGMwyt0me2hmC3sqStAaeMjwoUTf5nNhzDqMyZh3xNGmJxAYQ2POdFIlBWT9Yk-Q8k5TuBkVnkMps3ZXerds5pSwbbx5PLSIGQyJNw==), [4](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQHQ96BDLPvTmqOwcKqmUE6PnlzKdRmuhzzzgOzq--lm51T7tumRHkVRe-Z84COEJb4OSeXRDocTUovqYUv28w1aGSAU2WTjjREbTrsPMIc_2rXOakXVr9MWhSHH6aGq_R3z) " ;
    mtr:max_pgain "63612169.802555"^^xsd:float .

mtr:GCST90200272_GCST90200187 a mtr:MetaboliteRatio ;
    rdfs:label "3-hydroxyoctanoylcarnitine (1) to tetradecadienoate (14:2)*" ;
    mtr:has_denominator chebi:70719 ;
    mtr:has_numerator chebi:84100 ;
    mtr:llm_gene_phenotype_relationship " The THEM4 eQTL colocalizes with diverticular disease. Altered THEM4 expression may dysregulate fatty acid metabolism in the colon, impacting energy balance and inflammatory processes, which are implicated in the pathophysiology of diverticular disease.[7](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQEfpc2-QQf7J7bRJgy3sC2e-Ns_c9JNOeuxdpdRStxyD_HWEj2cL3UGJFPTJwQAj6sq5JmIOna0E_x_vFfdzRmwpFg54ceiMw3WkRErIWgV8ecP7aL2V0UT9-u2dniOUpmr5k9ZLDBiYnK-QJhpVqMHdAHfiNDz7d-TqefbrASTjUtTv8LhJdjpP5DlyCMDMfhOvn0=), [8](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQHpIGKCBO7swOFWVsIVBAZd0XMEWqi6qUCazDrufUpSXFEZ55lm-U4Pp6ADKUWYlaMTepnuk_YDGxHn-lENe_gFgauF-cKM085BBmHNye6YZBog6Z72LtILrbrphWnRejWULbM6gYWUmQv4Fr5UWrBM2bzPNQ-_PEz5svi9j5wg_k7ivuclWF3g516_qShX8T0FuYGQCaebN1VHWw==), [9](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQHp_sqi72qnTMWP5bfT7lADh4YFvjC5XFogZI-dVohrjloxPM75gxYu1sHIYBY3VUv5eISF50Ez-58MpyYoCr6o2LJD5Mls851YAWql1ZsQsMUV65X8zKwZ88CTskRXMwtYX4E=) " ;
    mtr:llm_phenotype_driver " Gene-centric:THEM4" ;
    mtr:llm_ratio_evidence " metabolites related through biology " ;
    mtr:llm_ratio_explanation " This ratio may reflect the balance between mitochondrial fatty acid beta-oxidation (numerator) and alternative fatty acid oxidation pathways (denominator), potentially influenced by THEM4 activity. " ;
    mtr:max_pgain "127797077924.1604"^^xsd:float .

mtr:GCST90200281_GCST90199652 a mtr:MetaboliteRatio ;
    rdfs:label "phosphoethanolamine to 1-stearoyl-2-oleoyl-gps (18:0/18:1)" ;
    mtr:has_denominator chebi:79096 ;
    mtr:has_numerator chebi:17553 ;
    mtr:llm_gene_phenotype_relationship " ALPL gene variants impact the enzymatic activity of its protein product, alkaline phosphatase (ALP).[4](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQHcS_D13rij-mFRY_obI8vLjZVdc7pC2anbGuApWwWczasfq6XYHpmkFA3bAoGrYDUN0Fi9Z-7FfLuNElAr75pebmRrmh0VTgFhwhLTetoLj-1ydUeAXEpEdRuSUDitrOQYZ_x9lAVRVdbdBrwEw9k_sbyyglM-hHDZM29m0lTyXk_VOPUl9Hpnkq1YoqPC5bY=), [5](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQHlfuRA1DxU0pCwWhlRVPElM53s2NnmpgEE2YBLQ_v4vIhq1bG06mhWsq_0HdYMfMZVAgjFHjebBFS9x4eaEQkBah0GIArc5IyGD8-K_1d78-L1RdloTk30o80ZJGw4jjY9OY-65Dw=) This directly alters levels of its substrate, phosphoethanolamine, and related phenotypes like serum calcium and ALP levels, reflecting ALPL's role in mineralization.[3](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQH25AOkj_keP76bN75Fr2oYHmsiswxp7lwsOzqi9nuuZKJsWscB0qTwJnDpTndOpzP_wPS9T7Q85jnzzSkKyXW-nUljUGjnduPnXjMohWdi3sK_b96SBsNbZX_XfmbdiUM=), [4](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQHcS_D13rij-mFRY_obI8vLjZVdc7pC2anbGuApWwWczasfq6XYHpmkFA3bAoGrYDUN0Fi9Z-7FfLuNElAr75pebmRrmh0VTgFhwhLTetoLj-1ydUeAXEpEdRuSUDitrOQYZ_x9lAVRVdbdBrwEw9k_sbyyglM-hHDZM29m0lTyXk_VOPUl9Hpnkq1YoqPC5bY=), [9](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQH3iKXFeJY3_y1R6mggQjCJ0NLrT4O74JznFMmbOjVY0x4EGb02T-Dzai0n6CgFDiAiP1Xvtnl7RBul_nFwbHamVWRpkZmCnt2TfYaA7J40PL3INParypKV8_0u4LywFPY8wywYm9R723sEffQfxhHUchSoh29THu5JkGGV0XO4Cs_5yqeEA59xQY4iNEQBJC2EN0UjzsO9Wij2ZdnDAHqc7yx9M2CqMiB1icaDER-wuA3n75dX22YcU-E=) " ;
    mtr:llm_phenotype_driver " Gene-centric:ALPL" ;
    mtr:llm_ratio_evidence " metabolites not in a pathway but enzyme catalyzes one metabolite " ;
    mtr:llm_ratio_explanation " Genetic variants in ALPL likely alter its substrate, phosphoethanolamine, relative to phosphatidylserine, reflecting changes in glycerophospholipid metabolism and ALPL enzymatic activity.[1](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQEt1FAwHYAeKZhYxs24zelKsmy9TjE9LQ1V9prQROVcH1ixGUznqVCaCr-L3dtNWabvOhUvTgRwtPSM0vk214yxY9ocdoAmZeqSeGE6qc8L9PZkkHVsjo8h_szWKaJa7VP-2JtTGqaLblA=), [4](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQHcS_D13rij-mFRY_obI8vLjZVdc7pC2anbGuApWwWczasfq6XYHpmkFA3bAoGrYDUN0Fi9Z-7FfLuNElAr75pebmRrmh0VTgFhwhLTetoLj-1ydUeAXEpEdRuSUDitrOQYZ_x9lAVRVdbdBrwEw9k_sbyyglM-hHDZM29m0lTyXk_VOPUl9Hpnkq1YoqPC5bY=) " ;
    mtr:max_pgain "143330181.2776215"^^xsd:float ;
    mtr:reaction_distance 3 .

mtr:GCST90200354_GCST90200187 a mtr:MetaboliteRatio ;
    rdfs:label "linoleate (18:2n6) to tetradecadienoate (14:2)*" ;
    mtr:has_denominator chebi:70719 ;
    mtr:has_numerator chebi:75108 ;
    mtr:llm_gene_phenotype_relationship " No phenotype link can be established as no associated phenotypes were provided in the input data. " ;
    mtr:llm_phenotype_driver " none" ;
    mtr:llm_ratio_evidence " metabolites not in a pathway but enzyme catalyzes one metabolite " ;
    mtr:llm_ratio_explanation " An elevated ratio may indicate altered beta-oxidation of linoleate, where tetradecadienoate is an intermediate, potentially influenced by THEM4's thioesterase activity on fatty acyl-CoAs.[1](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQGZNF5iEgBTAUD-H28K-7YCch6kKC5-xygii-3lRUPmkSNaFbudsVkuPse0rFWTb2BTkE7mFgc6HSqyaRhGR4Aed3U_9IIovRYfYkm1Hyn0eSnCZIBM5FLkOBozhg_PVknN2U2AEw-eg8BPqAxXrxMJMB732JCtIwfVSe8B0sQcjEeMm51oQWO6zFy4yf4aK-jQfMz8iPQlkmbqwJ6s05LoasgxsfNF), [8](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQEg3UmFBtiTqTZY68UZVJFAQDlHPExsjnEo9q0FMzgwHpy8nrKRP0F8yTFCK6z3zOqaV8-FDNRI2AceaqjxYMFTaPhClL3V9MVPXt_93yH_urpH-Rp8_tVDOg1Im6JYaJ_XsQ==) " ;
    mtr:max_pgain "3.115973151965226e+28"^^xsd:float .

