mtr:GCST90199735_GCST90199681 a mtr:MetaboliteRatio ;
    rdfs:label "n-acetylhistidine to 2-hydroxyoctanoate" ;
    mtr:has_numerator chebi:16437 ;
    mtr:llm_gene_phenotype_relationship " A missense variant in NAT8, an acetyltransferase, likely alters n-acetylhistidine levels.[1](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQFl_oS6JBnEphQC0GUaMiTNlxXU2eo56jajGGnQ670tzFIWe83JiWJR89-bKi7bqe7Mtd0fCRia-NPEXHdyPW4uCmcYmBcR7kQjpAcbdX1lHx4hmFvDbAvNbFpBvh7-7B6QLixgnYS1y2EVF-Y=), [3](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQE-_I0vpNolAvN5eDtBD2lDNqfJ0Dm7CbDWnnYoS5Iwdytx-U0sb_8ZYdbBwfjhcLtTDJylsuCCNBATDFmNqwO1Ikom2LyM2CBRwq338W9E1nVwZOHTKIF0jqrLv7M9pcoO_jHu8ErptZdwvL3-ozdNaZ44OMEeARP9oD2tI4epUjywXmYn9CwTJNmaqZBWjf2dvzug_rdv8cFyYS-D6f4frwCBvX2X), [8](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQELprYTu-mi3r3bzbxADzbn2P3Wc4h29KvJ2QR8M5z0Qf2Qa4XYBMbu3QsWi7FydktYRATOzlmTpghAjlA3eyCq2MPExWR4vFRXzIZf2JnSBN7dL5LCSfCAHDEyywxvrvXeQ70u) Both altered NAT8 function and n-acetylhistidine levels are independently associated with an increased risk of chronic kidney disease and renal failure, phenotypes characterized by elevated serum creatinine.[1](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQFl_oS6JBnEphQC0GUaMiTNlxXU2eo56jajGGnQ670tzFIWe83JiWJR89-bKi7bqe7Mtd0fCRia-NPEXHdyPW4uCmcYmBcR7kQjpAcbdX1lHx4hmFvDbAvNbFpBvh7-7B6QLixgnYS1y2EVF-Y=), [2](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQG7ucq5EPMb64FoJTwftXPC84Ej60IekUuME7HJZvKtyA9QUylnymbqn0M7clR9ShTMJDuEuMANGp0yFijRa-pdteqVXnDrI5RuCNQqkEtoHmMbUaSEO_1LqZvcITpgGv4VuesbyzgtjTKWujxlmmQpwhDgxlyFMZjoesnA9qI6eluG9XyebvssAAhWYZ67mJNKVsIZ-CXWGFKLmvlLgKfGf7oanPDU9N02vZc=), [9](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQHR0yOnuhc30HQLuwzjAaItmJ5QyH9FVWEHm4DnZjJhTiLLO8VZEUF1VK0ppb_tic6juLd_oLC0HGEWrATDcQpPPcidvcourX5xEmc12VsmxGB3SXmwWFoIfj-OKEOzq6nYUDCB920=), [10](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQH3pNIntpDM5cIvnO5A-mF-RoPmisLDuSwRL34YyzkLPkOWuHUOO7Cn02BbE-b8nD-z8H--P-1pPmDvtUTQKSMTnuy9-TGSypg-bnN0snwRN054CvTJ5DolsWFB-um_46OywIBU) " ;
    mtr:llm_phenotype_driver " Gene-centric:NAT8" ;
    mtr:llm_ratio_evidence " metabolites not in a pathway but enzyme catalyzes one metabolite " ;
    mtr:llm_ratio_explanation " The ratio reflects altered NAT8-mediated acetylation of histidine relative to fatty acid metabolism, both of which are implicated in kidney function. " ;
    mtr:max_pgain "2.991067647132561e+22"^^xsd:float .

