    mtr:llm_ratio_explanation " This ratio reflects medium-chain fatty acid beta-oxidation efficiency; impaired ACADM function may alter the balance between cis-4-decenoate and its oxidation intermediate 3-hydroxydecanoylcarnitine.[9](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQE5oedjA8lqdxjCLhCTrzduV-JRbIxwYt0vX39rvtTzPbtwCgFnmVdtX0_VnjOMsc75t9oynKfXVq_MSFFjwtEpxj5PvP5Yq7oXJcMcop14LqxDADTVpc9qdcYM7xix002QpAWR42O9), [10](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQE2qk2pMME-Z8f5Py8tPt_cdbQVs2hBMIuM5WhcF0IyjsuygSd4PBUj8FGOuzwqHyGTg5QgfHV3j0czWTk5Kr3aOwve0ibTV9UjRGHbu6z7He3vjyhI7ewlHmr_9j5Qg4GRga8=) " ;
    mtr:max_pgain "18838368745.5667"^^xsd:float .

mtr:GCST90200249_GCST90199807 a mtr:MetaboliteRatio ;
    rdfs:label "branched-chain, straight-chain, or cyclopropyl 12:1 fatty acid* to hexadecanedioate (c16-dc)" ;
    mtr:has_denominator chebi:73722 ;
    mtr:llm_gene_phenotype_relationship " The CYP4F2 variant, by altering fatty acid metabolism, contributes to dyslipidemia (e.g., elevated triglycerides) and an inflammatory state.[7](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQG4s1zNNYFUAIqWHaXEqdCd51ldZe5P93HQ9kljh81vL2KW1NSo6NR5pTBim7hRKAeu6U2NTda7ig1t0rn4XZ8MhNoKjxnVd0h6EQxO5hetoTlE7vx14dHs76jQVjeaDFgyfYFw7xXelm0RAQ8=), [8](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQGeBDBfcTWtMd4lyiRVdAuFttsehB3A5iKu_Floros1mZngnmEsBRqhkScddMRi876Qf35KmCvzQtds3oAK0eU8j_3xCjGOjs1OpA07vIEXES8GtpU_U4_eFQ9OcMXIIVqNRuKWPQngPPbpKsIyY7Lv1tjULlXteXDvkc8VDgviTFR-kQtxxTdfKB5X81ViQMLhM88da5hjAZRmUN-Zfq8gsV6znJFURlfRAJm7NqLtqQ==), [9](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQEhfzcVOWlY2ZXxTlbO3vnfODfOBvAoJsDVmxdanlkCfKkTD9NpoCewbuzFGSR_JLqjuwP0iBuKxIoOLLQbqw4O_Wy6itrBsZeNEN9z8CoouvWRTtohLp36XTtW1kC9LyjNP_dQ), [10](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQF6EeVgj_F6suUFwZIL8CxDsxsxUwUWNvkZMa-pkj3nvFn6MxOx0nRb2DVwOqz60zloEDvtyWQ8ikOe_Odep2rFSvptN8cEJtInuHmUSX1Nx_UR2nlnJcuDLZbokRqQ80MoqxfPVOkg8GQEqQa24QRGYhgkMVvqYRiWfpL0O21toc-1xfmN4nWgPUNzDYZMM0-MY1YerzRp_vAyqwAzkxfxKfb_cydN5Lh23p4P1BrER2u3IBjXT4F8JhBQxTY7) This dysregulation is associated with the development of coronary atherosclerosis and ischaemic heart disease.[7](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQG4s1zNNYFUAIqWHaXEqdCd51ldZe5P93HQ9kljh81vL2KW1NSo6NR5pTBim7hRKAeu6U2NTda7ig1t0rn4XZ8MhNoKjxnVd0h6EQxO5hetoTlE7vx14dHs76jQVjeaDFgyfYFw7xXelm0RAQ8=), [11](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQGrg3vEa-J0RWDdOXeYS5gRBOu3hcmnThJXMqk-kYsvJbskU5FZlhLtRGcYP6KweDg2zZWv2aRRZ9cziIvSUQDE1vtFuIhbshTQpka9qlzcHqEaX40oeRwV9NJnUa9YsFHRiQ==), [12](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQEHH2BS3RIKesyaws8A02e2-PP6fEAmZKJxXV2TooqZ-ilUbrwwXmnYrQ9CleWfVKbiPJ2XL2gNGKsj_Isxn-CRqw9aJgZdSlDnCnI1QzdQo7cpIe2TxAUlinjE8a0BlKlPWt4YSxRljRNsl_nfBAArB8X_iNlzzqWcSZRt0nYDrzozTV7A6Dg1-HALenrcljiniz5BcnvCMfzIsaelGjhEO-FNyUZncry87VIjmYHyOCnjbfq8QNMxpj_qHU6RjWI8AunEQhQ6hhXbFAcr-Q==), [13](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQEwkY18pR9TWVrdofa_yfL4zAS4BYoMIie5cRNGlC2KuInr2syaoP_WWoNWbuWgZFnUdWIoCHgQC0yB7K-EwKwDCHk7YN8AOJ3MvcCjudWhKgRNmXz-XWo1q21y750J7aDh1HySv16y8s1odfKV-37vQSsDwY2ZTD-WsJ-17DViRWuZ3toP4cMnBdi6_zOAKfssmrhlZq1TXGec89rBbBbGI5rCsXzota3VGZ68vbdyTwLCph9IjUQ7-gkQSD4Mw80=) " ;
    mtr:llm_phenotype_driver " Gene-centric:CYP4F2" ;
    mtr:llm_ratio_evidence " metabolites not in a pathway but enzyme catalyzes one metabolite " ;
    mtr:llm_ratio_explanation " An elevated ratio suggests a shift in fatty acid metabolism, where the degradation of 12:1 fatty acids might be altered relative to hexadecanedioate production, potentially influenced by CYP4F2 activity. " ;
    mtr:max_pgain "585212081.044537"^^xsd:float .

mtr:GCST90200314_GCST90200443 a mtr:MetaboliteRatio ;
