mtr:GCST90199852_GCST90199854 a mtr:MetaboliteRatio ;
    rdfs:label "5alpha-androstan-3beta,17alpha-diol disulfate to 5alpha-pregnan-3beta,20alpha-diol monosulfate (2)" ;
    mtr:has_numerator chebi:133101 ;
    mtr:llm_gene_phenotype_relationship " Genetic variants in SULT2A1 and AKR1C4, enzymes involved in steroid and bile acid metabolism, alter the balance of sulfated steroid metabolites.[8](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQEs339CCjj0_R7xGmHRcZEwOQVY9quvjAxQ1DGr6ssIjQlQM9N964zqpweXnwGlxcrV114WbqMZ2S9S4zmvb9lQBpjlFHGpjVSaeSlnY8M-r6PSOQQqHT2mbMwslQ4NOnCs37Aux-hSQLwWm21AfW9P7IAhjgM=), [2](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQGc0Vn86F7JrbhnNE9J4p1b1Cc7bpPHbE7SZP1_YDwJD0Jvi7qPP78s3sTkhAbPFvXqGGK6BNqOQbhhdYUNRsSdrLw-AMxuDJvmjW2iUT0PlYbvjxzhIbIidsX33vklemonQ-ObazXayNWb), [10](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQHp0q6na6vDHVwCDg44J9OZpVMd9BzO6EZIJwsF9p6KcIzV4LLLgzkbiDmFjaS-ONdaKkitHPRiebOIhMI5vde0E55p9Y2TfyWD1e7LTyjRV_9UdCUxw0ZJN-vV0-AKIeo4R4_ZV1c7SqRoDRk=), [11](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQEm77TeuP7p-xu56iJBqT6z6Ju9C2J9i6lvORdBw6HvJ1sHX-__XfeONyT3cqA73ixwqJnH4PnckJ7_cK0mO7mul5m1uIOQpd3FYXMVCzZWMwvvpDMWHoeLMlFXfQ4GLNph5sR39WweeFU98cuCBtLWGtosZNTDzW0lCAOW) This imbalance contributes to bile supersaturation with cholesterol, a key factor in the formation of gallstones (cholelithiasis).[12](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQHS7q0F4jAh8d8uGiz35GSqgjt82E7mXQvQiGHTlw3ig3vnNXslDEBHGwz7dWqlx3yRU4jW6s0rje4zLb8JcsP-qdzqJyBOlPcV9Xyvd3sOZb6s5X2ek6T2Td6erBcBjrPSAydn82vcEQ==), [13](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQGJOkhTCzaDjlmvTB3HAhvq-Ma1T_X4-pRsIa8iqxVL8qMtwfxhaaTtvv0D2pHIvGZ-zBwEL6Hkx77Ogoa3JRsZTP3MERCW_MIpbVB83_vEunxRAQOpYu4MYsTHJ6hfeHCwVGbl2Y70ZndNzlQ=), [10](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQHp0q6na6vDHVwCDg44J9OZpVMd9BzO6EZIJwsF9p6KcIzV4LLLgzkbiDmFjaS-ONdaKkitHPRiebOIhMI5vde0E55p9Y2TfyWD1e7LTyjRV_9UdCUxw0ZJN-vV0-AKIeo4R4_ZV1c7SqRoDRk=) " ;
    mtr:llm_phenotype_driver " Gene-centric:SULT2A1" ;
    mtr:llm_ratio_evidence " metabolites related through biology " ;
    mtr:llm_ratio_explanation " This ratio reflects the balance between androgen and progesterone metabolite sulfation, activities influenced by both AKR1C4 in steroid reduction and SULT2A1 in sulfoconjugation.[3](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQGLgL1vjnM0cg4fT_ieqmRILwd70zGKb-U_orpMUIABsRwvoprTBfiBzcjcYxc2Pk3VRT4BU5hbfDf0Sfnel7Fd1ppYp5drjF9-xQAYtgbnd-xr5mrAYLppy1dUfy7Ftg==), [8](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQEs339CCjj0_R7xGmHRcZEwOQVY9quvjAxQ1DGr6ssIjQlQM9N964zqpweXnwGlxcrV114WbqMZ2S9S4zmvb9lQBpjlFHGpjVSaeSlnY8M-r6PSOQQqHT2mbMwslQ4NOnCs37Aux-hSQLwWm21AfW9P7IAhjgM=), [9](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQHVLhOxx4HNuMqcpkBEV57DBeG3MseCEKA2C1a7pebcipaYTwWvJ7cxsdc64wJn60LlMDnr7E0Sp0ap752bC-ytufXJLmghQb44fxNn2vEFYuwYWcAcgAKdjxEIDUcM3fkm1N6GwZAlmyqW4p4=) " ;
    mtr:max_pgain "2.824126296906732e+27"^^xsd:float .

mtr:GCST90199919_GCST90200697 a mtr:MetaboliteRatio ;
    rdfs:label "alliin to n2-acetyl,n6,n6-dimethyllysine" ;
    mtr:llm_gene_phenotype_relationship " ALMS1 is associated with ciliary function crucial for kidney health, and its disruption, along with NAT8 variants linked to kidney disease, likely drives the observed chronic kidney disease phenotype, with the metabolite ratio being a downstream marker.[1](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQEwwCK6yTY_gwH0Uug5pb9WE3D74Oi8DCGY4xo-1P_Kwoqi2S1dawH1eeEocUhlzwgpqd9WJFE2QnxUmomPkLzMwrO7vmvf4LkdGl2RllJq7CQffgT1CT-SFMSLO5I=), [4](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQGCTYo5-GgYWFVv5k6u_yOd7l_T2mOF8UI1OZelJoTNy_iqoVPqcJDiEcr7Z3BMoEzI7jRwQIF5hCeOrsdG_H1M0lX3t_771abZWBMVxczE84Ms4yjK5gW006c0), [2](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQEgOQre7I4kkT4DFj94i3-NXM0ZY4qhxNfYuZr-RHatOU5Usn9VNEQnc-5ImAExJfN16UPcK8zqHjszidKOvto7_dotOtseDrXIXSBRVyrP4ERLGJtQFX0f_bnz8EKRvimAH1l9QJDjQdTwEj5C_hGm8_AqjUmd7h56QQ==), [3](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQHTV-Yxv18JAzynWTE5KxDOSH_ggIidU09ihEklDkMQ2I4wJmIqcQq9VV2JdkKbrfkE1ieQHPPAYQDsC-mxivENnhjvz_WlpCHVNnCi8a9NJWRZL1xBWzDkqdVy848wOFAhZRUmkg==) " ;
    mtr:llm_phenotype_driver " Gene-centric:ALMS1" ;
    mtr:llm_ratio_evidence " metabolites related through biology " ;
    mtr:llm_ratio_explanation " The ratio may reflect altered kidney function where ALMS1 dysfunction impacts renal processes, and NAT8's role in acetylating amino acids is also implicated in kidney disease. " ;
    mtr:max_pgain "912831550875.9427"^^xsd:float .

mtr:GCST90200042_GCST90199893 a mtr:MetaboliteRatio ;
    rdfs:label "oleate/vaccenate (18:1) to cis-4-decenoate (10:1n6)*" ;
    mtr:has_denominator chebi:32380 ;
    mtr:has_numerator chebi:28727 ;
    mtr:llm_gene_phenotype_relationship " none " ;
    mtr:llm_phenotype_driver " none" ;
    mtr:llm_ratio_evidence " metabolites not in a pathway but enzyme catalyzes one metabolite " ;
    mtr:llm_ratio_explanation " An increased ratio of long-chain (oleate/vaccenate) to medium-chain (cis-4-decenoate) fatty acids may indicate impaired medium-chain beta-oxidation, a process involving ACADM.[1](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQGu_ixWYlXHn1zJnkrqmnfnGHZF92nSEosLT9GwIA80luVNF-bUMrR3hV4cPovzjyhdHf193m1iq4g0X6rh2fzVz8YnwcnM0IB1UcNfkULs5Qo_NbemzwR_oJ27oaM4Hp3iE06OFmiu), [7](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQFsutrKwhvUsasSDGvzeBwAaGNUuQ0Cyh6MEfhqo6TKjtldXz02DFa-743B65uJWDaZJaStfga_eXNFdbP8CltSPz6yLbF7_0VPpYI8Ptcv1uEM27BBJGo0DkjRRkGU3NL2LHg=) " ;
    mtr:max_pgain "4.064402982363529e+47"^^xsd:float .

