mtr:GCST90199821_GCST90199770 a mtr:MetaboliteRatio ;
    rdfs:label "1-linoleoyl-gpi (18:2)* to 1-arachidonylglycerol (20:4)" ;
    mtr:has_denominator chebi:34071 ;
    mtr:has_numerator chebi:133077 ;
    mtr:llm_gene_phenotype_relationship " Genetic variants in FADS1 and FADS2 alter the efficiency of polyunsaturated fatty acid synthesis.[3](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQEAD5ebCLZnk1xhJa_oAqQSbXVA7crm_70ZJ4y2aB5uq6iKyOEuHugDgf1yd1zcfHOj2BsM7wQ70Um09x8Y8sL74gLfjJ2BE5XuWqt1hqzopGauQXJflIayMrolSjtDzJhkZDY9REFi2n3NRzfN-Pny8WTSXyKfmITtWMJbOc4kmew1UYfKhVJyGaPiDrMJ), [10](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQHkIBC3g5ybi8codJXs78roVjMqmfIt-rgAohrv7tIplHGjdnXkdOp4FOiT6NNaR0rLjbHzOTBS73KNzzTGe01KFKQF6bTZm7F7lCOj3GjB95_tXVhCzxA3IjG2-3E2hQBKdXK1) This impacts the levels of arachidonic acid, a key component of 1-arachidonylglycerol and a precursor for inflammatory mediators, thus influencing the risk for inflammatory and metabolic disorders like cholelithiasis and type 2 diabetes.[11](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQGVIGSmqDdBtrx5cvYOaDj67nWFxfwmHfunK8qC87n2Ql0xEZhh9_hTfztQT-dzWF8q8MQGgkfNsdXOFfzfjCCNdwkM8b_04pHiwEdSPblGZDwb8_oQF5EdxPzPuZKQv6PmIR8DqWc-rGOvqbEKMPZIA84mjlhGKNRjsWpwXM8ILA6F-zq6XqncpZQEM6aSd99M7jrKQ0PsXPfP77uJHYY=), [2](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQFkxn16OXafLQFB3hd0jCXdurCIbVyjxVIcD-qZxw0o3VM-uLMhLY9UvemQBpTYqFIAHvgXGuz0UlaFwazMl6DU8pNWUIDQNhjO7vWEg_PoQNjX4yj781q0qv2g05GgwH52_Rj-7PFsTUa3GPY=), [12](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQE7pPd4mbqqrvXL4ao1_6SfNlRXMblyd7zWKo_6vPdoDOIt2RlQC25SIF1gw6fDu-ch_ejDcXi9eaxkDl2ct3_9lz5TMqHPyDaHKHaQ4pmUudIQRnSVoV6yb4MipeX3erq6hxV-Ot2wGJ6NuaYJ_UYewptEHe8KCYqyFjvU5jC4d7LH9XiucyElPtrqL-cLDd40GS_9n5ESddPDTDEY6IjNJNxAMDDuYHXvHXJWCmaUW8R_6Q==), [13](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQF48rpGWwE-v29kJkanO2EGKMpwrkg2facq27JlKtKEdRlWfJPkW7dT7bsyB6SHxuy68WJNBGoLwiYa6LqGGiTb453UymoE_8m2gqMOSaL-FMDBSxYYcvvsbblfh3OsNyC4D8KMB2exdTcOCupvDbrM8lM6bPxQhtUU7q85hzSxayFBlBU7lvUK0lnn5k_C3BsuDgURBJU-lzC6pUJGmMEEnvvXMexQi70=) " ;
    mtr:llm_phenotype_driver " Gene-centric:FADS1" ;
    mtr:llm_ratio_evidence " metabolites not in a pathway but enzyme catalyzes one metabolite " ;
    mtr:llm_ratio_explanation " The ratio reflects the balance between glycerophosphoinositol and endocannabinoid pathways, where higher FADS1/2 activity favors the formation of arachidonic acid (a precursor to 1-arachidonylglycerol). " ;
    mtr:max_pgain "3.695458741288937e+42"^^xsd:float .

mtr:GCST90199910_GCST90200067 a mtr:MetaboliteRatio ;
    rdfs:label "1-(1-enyl-stearoyl)-gpe (p-18:0)* to 1-stearoyl-2-linoleoyl-gpi (18:0/18:2)" ;
    mtr:llm_gene_phenotype_relationship " Genetic variation in FADS1/FADS2 alters PUFA metabolism, impacting the composition of complex lipids.[11](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQFS1d82wbHnxYISNJctkjd3GXaFMBr5nTWfvz21IZuphyFsH7l8AzGzUQWibzxf69I5fqv_CzH02eX41KKmr7a_qltVVtf_zRAwZm-D5abQai4c3ElcfhAeH7cMe2wB4wahEbVohofV1k_w7TvOiE6YnO70cP9shAyzeP2oH3Qbt6PrgLpXRE7ej-TxDQ==), [12](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQEXGlIKQvlC-rvak3DTx6nh-Yis1FxLXz0MCo95ZCgb6tVSt1BttPd8WMCkw7XvNvWaQQJ6atKWlj6qq4-GXcx-9XpcX0a6mIy2DN6PP6xPDOnIDrLJnxyvOE2wnwE7BZsFpuIHYUv6hbzyUAqv0oxy7jb1oBRmEQTCwCM73oAo3HFA7jUzF7_l4HxiZTve_4wp8kMNHW6gj2QHg_KJisb5M7_M-FQ9y3bKDC227r396rzp_17E2ciEokwhU7Qbq-KTKbEY6j7j7AZemec=), [13](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQEpaLsbEgxyNoMIzHY9NTNybKhYJSxwWvJlALv8vpGZ9j-nZmB65c-Et8RSS0w1hQXauWnd64NAvXPqOBkgJ_DraEUJWVTY2Ez__Bown3GzfAF8Dc51yCIk6KQdVfaKWzalT2Xl8KqI68ZEnFI=), [14](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQE5oweDGyChsSWT3TYr4VEWY5xmNN7zNwGDRDzZeaiU-ROeGLayabdI_sw0emVKiJ8qdyRbIWLfARlICQ7OcWSv3mvPXPu8YGo6VsL8he3jEnOpD-0IWvS-N47oq9D5FBG_qqnc) This dysregulation is associated with altered inflammatory responses and lipid profiles, contributing to the risk of cardiovascular diseases, type 2 diabetes, and inflammatory conditions like IBD.[15](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQExwciuA4RCrwvRKlaomJ0YWa395gdPztSvH6FUZYY-YcrqC_xkGCPAj1qxP8vOlFtyoiZpQ4Wwc5eluuV5qChF8sf1aKKlgB7xwUN7OsSpN4JuXEjfMJX60yM09YYkv2isfal1Chi0-GwzA9s=), [16](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQGQ1Jc3_Fd-1oOxuWALF2xGNCsMWEPT7y4nz-wIc4rSq4M3TPHxhCwEA1IEJaFL6vD3CRYr1npugRZ9VRUEh5kNRhorW5slf6GxgN65B2f5enGaRU-ENBOpfVdDXLvhs9xeU5HI), [17](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQHUZt-0jm73oWVj3hjLjKK7Itotyn1saxkRrNNNyi7tCWHeygsV6iHXemPbrikqGVhCetLk46d5Umo7LB89w0OA8MP2MMYxdN-KnvP-gXzsFKgcE7Dcc-qt0ZOSxzQNS4ybHiQcL9F-8Ec-8udo), [18](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQEHLy9A3F1sQXyRoyxHVdFYFqMcr2XW2I7inZmXBf29jXr9cEoWZ1CLBpntWp7tXzI4thAEbBCkf7mFiMYD1JkakJcdlWpQX-r317Evc5kg4UJ7_ap1kDi_h6pRma76hEi9X9iORmdNDRumdaw=), [19](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQH2OkRGdyV10hB2ZJsKd5Zkmca-OTsNlVzqtDpuLyCckG3wiv9guJMGN9YICgtrWDxOj_qUS844CeZZnDSKmrcL597d3fGjeNUxixsIM356lT3QfMTp), [20](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQGeE3AVUyi-ZIVJ8Ircsj56T-83GEsKc_CX0VzRLBBC5MRsFIISlrcB5lVXRrOUH1s3IaXe5M8YGsjYgBeA-UkvCRpAnmznUc9x9ukLBCrdJYcWqKeLUs9TAYRU6GNyiYYGXfqUC4PmJ1D-GQqFfm8o0UoEXlSD0QodBHi2mYZRx2Okx4IshBGS), [21](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQEfamDgWmJj3gGoubMl6UZQFHLcFqNMhfJb14S2SR76Srvjqe7ehyGW9HZuYeQWpNKtpSFHJ3CDU2eEkWGjocUFdvTDRODsdZetsazThIu39Q93CPt6NPGO25J9Nu9nt_BDcGrMdDbuZs9DeOw=) " ;
    mtr:llm_phenotype_driver " Gene-centric:FADS1/FADS2" ;
    mtr:llm_ratio_evidence " metabolites not in a pathway but enzyme catalyzes one metabolite " ;
    mtr:llm_ratio_explanation " The ratio reflects the balance between ether phospholipid and phosphatidylinositol synthesis, potentially influenced by FADS desaturase activity on fatty acid precursors for both lipids. " ;
