    mtr:llm_gene_phenotype_relationship " FADS1/FADS2 gene variants influence the conversion efficiency of fatty acids, affecting the balance of plasmalogens.[1](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQGp9sqHmbJFkpBmbH5P_Otys5JrWsm13etYJ1pQehT2yHDQ5ppJIh4KUfTXfk_GDVU8o8Fc4PGhK5TXK0pB7jSk9hfGBgzSI55PkfpVPz7AIxmx_9FI2p2ocKgU2FXVd-NPYG4iCSe_PFCrqe4iIlfQjdvOyV1fXePtRK8UFvRH3xq4SbyezX5SYdUp81oz), [8](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQHwVZ9rzcs8JEqu-YN27_os-7HLLGZsgFcfSGh0k4mgXZTF8CO8m6CMHmdPLwKyIdncuixjY9f8qWgqafqkkmWtvA5j3uoMHdHPy1CXsxv7KDBZK2fqmr5PIb64-0GtyeQ0-3GD), [9](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQE7f-QSVxoYaFAEBlX7a_V4ethENMil9dc4gjfsWA9ydfPhXQekk5q-uQNwt1H3FkSdvwmcP_dHZd16KyskJJ0V3gbMLqQR9mdVH2_vUqMy1qfW39LwP9j0pRj9RECIuD1Ed8TX37Ma7DriaFI=) This altered lipid profile is associated with cholesterol levels and inflammatory conditions like asthma and dermatitis, linking genetic predisposition to metabolic and disease phenotypes.[10](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQEWF0vweLnpOaN3piqcpeWJQLdL6TgQ4fOtKYScGuf93waSuMDqIXYFbThRwwQt_ARYfB6li2KKxujPU76u39d8dPevOx7Y6UXSSeKu26IPkhb15SUpexS5wJGU_7YRKiOYexYB), [11](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQG1ohchihXc-TCPzh74zPm99zuZnBBjgrFkd0JfnZVSqSzFE6Uq2lh1HPxXYTJ3wV5AR7XgkBRv8ftuLe_QymliN8uFMpi3VLEhWNq_Q6u3pI0NvkYtq2AKaX5Mq1wUCPZwytq16hIozLRFY2MbJOdE6k9MUcxHik7DI5SMC23hlpHSIyVrCmGDq6smcxSG4WfilL2dwuBtmGynQ9lu5mYcb_bOBbsE_vsTX__gwbtuHqx69QJ4UVExKMqDKBcp7zfhIo0gx5YRPKkvMJWICM7SGexokEJ97Gwhr74aWMk=), [12](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQEKgFOZFrz9AdzG6E0rkOdPdqNEdRpmMeiJ3e5uUm4clfYn3CJ4eGNAuluWOwIhFqn7iooDDh9hn_JcvtY93s3ji4NjFXgVaEVLkUWO0OLdX3nCOdzY6m3pt3G9iYW9diLazmSDQOq0E0-ZvSk=), [13](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQEPdaVj5BKHk8emb1sH1FdN7ZS-rdUO-BfOv3XOf8nR2xvclynTP13qHZ3nYhRD_M7t9XcSxDxHnwth9eAvKWUZDp6dQzMp8YhQ8BB0ASRvNT8pXWs1LdsM1Pn1MzagdopXUxNLDIz1DiyWA_D_mTv-szcruiyyEnrDlsiUYDItvr73s7Q=) " ;
    mtr:llm_phenotype_driver " Gene-centric:FADS1/FADS2" ;
    mtr:llm_ratio_evidence " reaction where the ratio is shared through a pathway " ;
    mtr:llm_ratio_explanation " The ratio reflects FADS1/FADS2 activity, where higher activity favors the synthesis of arachidonic acid (20:4) for the numerator over oleic acid (18:1) incorporation.[1](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQGp9sqHmbJFkpBmbH5P_Otys5JrWsm13etYJ1pQehT2yHDQ5ppJIh4KUfTXfk_GDVU8o8Fc4PGhK5TXK0pB7jSk9hfGBgzSI55PkfpVPz7AIxmx_9FI2p2ocKgU2FXVd-NPYG4iCSe_PFCrqe4iIlfQjdvOyV1fXePtRK8UFvRH3xq4SbyezX5SYdUp81oz), [7](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQGUskqqCK3wVWvphGBnCHyuTyLWR0wiYNnaLzR4Vo3eQh6y8kIOWCA8f2PAVmn5wWaaeBhG3C3C2q6jtk4DXp4HZLyEePV_520ZuaN1edHhbpEQ_camoWAjZ1UiWq-oGKgnGGxAMYHjYSzZGfqfmnDba-0M0_n5kyvdyGTW-XT6BNPlvA==) " ;
    mtr:max_pgain "9.464973696279496e+17"^^xsd:float .

mtr:GCST90200107_GCST90199751 a mtr:MetaboliteRatio ;
    rdfs:label "gamma-glutamyl-alpha-lysine to gamma-glutamylmethionine" ;
    mtr:llm_gene_phenotype_relationship " Genetic variation in the amino acid transporter SLC7A6 likely alters the cellular availability of lysine and methionine.[1](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQEPyIMkbpQMbgOaDMJQ3OEuG9BlaH0y61aBzPt46MFRRr6_5rkTFmyohjurWIv75dzygCP_Q13kLTDphn4bGGbjrh2ebeIVJIzhmYGLvdnMn2K9DFzP-5kkCYdu2VlpGZUJeygsTNyBIVok10t1cNU6D45N) This can impact downstream processes such as protein metabolism and the gamma-glutamyl cycle, potentially influencing renal function (serum creatinine) and immune cell homeostasis (eosinophil count).[8](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQE_qEzFw1mp9Vh2DCvcWUqs6LU236aKBdnE5GqD9rtysKYM3KL6WuTwqcz4gS7h6gczLfo6flymQFZZ49xoxBpwvfTf30rYk_r2JjM0rHxaZ4zg53k0ENLZ8gxXZSomGYF_), [9](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQG1LIm6OkRxXxhhIw7Sff8mrXH2dEUXIY8FaCCrKRYz86X2QJfAtVUWmn6s58-kIaQEoSFbre1TkNMoAudhyzzNGqy-CiYX99w3Z7RIMVcgMUWlq9iD1mwHlmhhe6Q04WKmdEUPxN3OaCJOSTkfXMScU5ekDFTRhUbPAsM0i88=) " ;
    mtr:llm_phenotype_driver " Gene-centric:SLC7A6" ;
    mtr:llm_ratio_evidence " metabolites related through biology " ;
    mtr:llm_ratio_explanation " The ratio reflects the relative transport of lysine and methionine by SLC7A6, and subsequent metabolism via the gamma-glutamyl cycle. " ;
    mtr:max_pgain "55192297.63072784"^^xsd:float .

mtr:GCST90200243_GCST90199876 a mtr:MetaboliteRatio ;
    rdfs:label "hydroxypalmitoyl sphingomyelin (d18:1/16:0(oh))** to palmitoyl sphingomyelin (d18:1/16:0)" ;
    mtr:has_denominator chebi:78646 ;
    mtr:llm_gene_phenotype_relationship " FADS1 gene variants are linked to altered lipid profiles and an increased risk for inflammatory conditions like IBD and metabolic disorders such as type 2 diabetes[6](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQE5HFhxJVAX8fkqVVa94zYCHiXfNEk3w0dAgeUbf9kU0VMdt-K3iLeMAvb2uHJh2EREgkJCas2XNU2jkvpGQWEPqltkFXTB6mt9EEw-L3uXun4XCJod_U3NXMMpfpx_rVAtMQ==), [7](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQH_SFp1U-4b3sqSxWkH62sCTov1zxnbuUwGWeZ3YTWCZ3oBSgIEx4zVf-xQa-WmQzboVIJbgTiMMWRqZhegIO2uWHoFe5yZip6wf_X-u4TuIjtwa0_8EXlFkX2NVzbhKRyeF3dzgJryU7CYvZyib9bfCn1laYFuOMo4EPBtDuoECVFHG7oXK7zroLiUhVWUfcqR), [8](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQHXiiI_rZyVlC9Bqbqag-txRVohefx66vl3revjtbW_unz2pwyIpmGYVqjr-wZMOvPRkrvP6-2mQfW-CQtpQCmBXyXsS4Bl1BVE7AnIJgraCVFhnXmQu9719Fq2Gs8-UeN3i_byosxVjZuf_rg=), [9](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQHAyK4MUk0kPeHbQF02VvH-4-b8ueJ8rkPyL-m4ugGjJjxVu7ro6zEpH7RXFzwThLhdI29Mi3Ia60W1JHQ9_tu7CSFZ-2rAKdMTs-cQ_Z-zoJKvlRf3Hg-aRrlbcyWg2P_4Ty-3), potentially through changes in sphingolipid composition, which is associated with valvular heart disease.[10](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQE6l9ad-ksS08qDcMAOjtZQ_HeJftw8XW6s9G11VVF9HjIsRrwfSf45iwaaOvI3iqsNF7oNEJCiLiMb6V7T0IXA_BDX_LA1O45e8NKxY6StQcK85Rrqba8eAgjAZThcE8RBNwBTBk8yZG0SIc0=), [11](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQEIkCKCPe3Qb08gwmhu1RgFeBVkhsKeNdGcKhqDGYwvM4kRUaNxJ3MPZFcHfwRWiXb6jkGlaK2PtW-H_XR-4TyFMavSonHfvbSbstREAdXgVV1gngUg0WsT9LuAc74GRwI48URqOJ6i77WQSWp9z3Ip7MI0WA6LkAAIDjIryQrIczE_FbIquztEacUoZcpwF_n-MmsrqZKe-Ijyri2RaTAF4dhSy6gaWkwn5JYfLpIvLqf_oa090tsqHNUZ07Yzt5eTzw==), [12](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQHE8RSfDc2_hXJHpQt_hz162OVfZzRiC2hF-FpiLf97HY_bavCrIcItUIbWQ_rTWZTqQpQzqviCzEoPIQdtxbo-c-wzo_DAiYcRpIa1sSV5sB3iEbMZtBjIONVB9hFIch2yVdseUL35Lzn1GsWHIj1eI6I1qp0=), [13](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQEZsm3p6JPZ0aMIFSe0F3j9bdet-jIgUI61_N9dn6_3Y26EUKg7xpX5L86OBdQFmQ7AvR3LNvUAUJWAsNkjL_5Zanjpq06xlb16oUNKQRa5KcvyxU9ePHPnWYN_oNQE8ibRi-4DX52VKZLAdCIFLMkqoPKBsDX6cQ==) " ;
