    mtr:llm_gene_phenotype_relationship " Genetic variants in FADS1 alter its enzymatic efficiency, impacting levels of arachidonic acid and its downstream inflammatory mediators.[11](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQGGe_SqttGDdpfzENo-cHz-DrbfJBQWbUTf_FblClpuQTLpVKWeIytWqDR07wIhWC65KcBmf_MFSQv1u7nlmN8J3pKtZKBAuMOW1JPpDPuKpN99CN5B0EoB3wqlyXKZpxpwgM_YGJdTjadCAB_PjWwFwMNXjjo=), [12](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQFNHCFGzUuwT5NsVON9aOXa6MqaP25Oqh7K3JUzD1Pne_dHHWSMUXANBcLOuJtbaAd1asrWvPuoylh4aHizi1ogFdE__Xs2ywZYUudQR7E_69dPJq3H) This dysregulation of lipid metabolism is linked to phenotypes like hypercholesterolemia, type 2 diabetes, and cholelithiasis.[13](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQG5WdbSHuey38sguQpHv56KXSXzizWOYI0daa1FNgT4XxXAavAyJcP28Hp9rqFHGMPNCN0XK8UVDLlE9FPCF6kxc3d8U2Cfkep_LEfDahAqDHX5n-8dG6WMHUWcU20r-9ED7A==), [11](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQGGe_SqttGDdpfzENo-cHz-DrbfJBQWbUTf_FblClpuQTLpVKWeIytWqDR07wIhWC65KcBmf_MFSQv1u7nlmN8J3pKtZKBAuMOW1JPpDPuKpN99CN5B0EoB3wqlyXKZpxpwgM_YGJdTjadCAB_PjWwFwMNXjjo=), [14](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQGr8Y2OpBHOVXnOWeqX1nw9T7-hlIpQQmV6ObflGemNHRQfuPBpc-hy-_G1xcamtRLGnSQpnFMfvekSxJHCyAXNNBKOAd6BUHJuaTpuSNFuu7v40G5YRcQZadHdaOoc5MvxG10z), [15](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQF5dwzi-983bzG5Exhv-KucdKRe0L3XYm2GY8BHYP_hFysYTFtF4cjEsXEV6f779cVqhFvRlnYeFEFrQghFltoEczO2l_R1FPhYSYWJFMWo777dhsfDjLcZkNEL6yr4ujoNai-J1GM=) " ;
    mtr:llm_phenotype_driver " Gene-centric:FADS1" ;
    mtr:llm_ratio_evidence " metabolites not in a pathway but enzyme catalyzes one metabolite " ;
    mtr:llm_ratio_explanation " The ratio reflects FADS1 activity; lower FADS1 function decreases arachidonic acid (denominator), thus increasing the ratio of sphingomyelin to this specific phosphatidylcholine. " ;
    mtr:max_pgain "1.236021054356921e+30"^^xsd:float .

mtr:GCST90200054_GCST90200063 a mtr:MetaboliteRatio ;
    rdfs:label "1-palmitoyl-2-arachidonoyl-gpe (16:0/20:4)* to 1-palmitoyl-2-docosahexaenoyl-gpe (16:0/22:6)*" ;
    mtr:has_denominator chebi:78261 ;
    mtr:llm_gene_phenotype_relationship " Genetic variation in FADS1 alters enzyme activity, impacting the balance of pro-inflammatory omega-6 and anti-inflammatory omega-3 fatty acids.[1](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQEhtqKNCkf-rE2Uh3j6YRc1f_gkqtxX9znI7cycyTS74CDCHzMTlRSbNrkz1-4-bAPKlvv2ua1z1YcsLWlInYvTR9ABQ1WOGk_6IfGnqPNQDPgt-PQJ9x7-xMtSr89g), [7](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQFRtrHRPihtKey992O1SPZZANSZ6Gom2gEGf4q-K4cFtNzPxgsq83lFozWhlp2HpOsBc6Cs_q4kcFa4lWY7oyeTA38wA_gYNxShkiR-oXv-ts3a-Cod), [8](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQHtYLp03bRt-WFouJ8fAJDrfYbKPqbfuo2Qeh7xEaTMrCLLnAadMI7FbqN97L14huhuWD6QaMthsGROmeXmG5vxunzr1bCx_MGP2YKDnwssn6GI65aiaT3vzIFDuNvyCnA71lcxZGYFTVg3xmlx) This shift can influence lipid metabolism and inflammatory responses seen in asthma, dermatitis, and hypercholesterolemia.[9](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQE13I8bYqvzJ3fmNCFXOhf0g3pIq9NXRve5O7GxcZ4bD4GWo23e8qE-jhs1O-BcuewIKGZkje54FPjCqD_yvwGqUkLBXMEG1POBKmHz2dqy2BL3EcSVxNFLy2iq_YWLTvGcj4s5tCBH_v1XpD8=), [10](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQG8y_cw6WxzwSZe146eyZkOUjBkgCDiqwwDKDiNkj8OIRJd0BbDWR1QSwznbJZN7NtSiOj0jsKHhwjX7wfURE-KGvuwn88XAzUPbTHutTkPwpT6zArxKh4j77502P_zaf8pRcyEkbRSOvuezls=), [7](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQFRtrHRPihtKey992O1SPZZANSZ6Gom2gEGf4q-K4cFtNzPxgsq83lFozWhlp2HpOsBc6Cs_q4kcFa4lWY7oyeTA38wA_gYNxShkiR-oXv-ts3a-Cod) " ;
    mtr:llm_phenotype_driver " Gene-centric:FADS1" ;
    mtr:llm_ratio_evidence " reaction where the ratio is shared through a pathway " ;
    mtr:llm_ratio_explanation " This ratio reflects the balance between omega-6 (arachidonic acid) and omega-3 (docosahexaenoic acid) containing phosphatidylethanolamines, modulated by FADS1 enzyme activity in PUFA synthesis. " ;
    mtr:max_pgain "1.60900175906025e+20"^^xsd:float .

mtr:GCST90200067_GCST90200125 a mtr:MetaboliteRatio ;
    rdfs:label "1-stearoyl-2-linoleoyl-gpi (18:0/18:2) to sphingomyelin (d17:2/16:0, d18:2/15:0)*" ;
    mtr:llm_gene_phenotype_relationship " Genetic variants in FADS1/FADS2 alter fatty acid desaturation, affecting the composition of glycerophospholipids and sphingolipids.[9](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQHnxv_ZiWg_J5AWkIaNUpD9bOkDIGvjrfRqVGJAsciCFtbvR_ezfhQsseXcWBH5OwT0WXH1X6Vd3evlQTq_n5PQOZb80KnLds6PM-qvsmChxQctA9__tn87pmmfw4a111xBNh5Bf-vfvC4Q0bGh7YX9RV_PhT-gXMmUiTno7CWVW2hEdk_m5fSyDhzF23oBNw==), [10](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQGIey-iRWc80A2jOzngvjS-kejgrrEv9js65KqN4ZIvZOU4w_QIvQgV9sH7ed6s4_kGwGfbkC85gKlKpC1lCX4wwK4uEYa_Hvo6sd_tAbA7xnoGJUHY), [11](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQEF3ZBB-XUHoS2jmJquX-XkCNlrk_kx2rx9wx_He8kvjnGhJbHAvVz_Gi0C2ppaLfLARMpxZpbz7b_Ywed94ZlFNSHP07Mghk1P1PWrRMmqnObXDWitt1Xa1g6oSmAcXn7cL1DXY5P267OO7iE=) This dysregulation is associated with an increased risk for inflammatory conditions, hypercholesterolemia, and cholelithiasis.[12](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQFjihLmoCPWOZUuaM-yaRAj8aFUzrPpVuWqgi-9oTMPcJ8ECI-EzW6b_6vWwlVVFQw30aYFaRpu9W7BeliPC6JupvrjxFbIehxCduHrjVEQtbqZxh2K3sag_PCSX4dIA3t9rMOajTzJCR3vqCs=), [5](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQF35FM8iqvU4zD0G9PNuzF0THc4DXVq9jI1G701fhJGkM1xGY-Bs0pccqIXmsP76dGniKX-kR-gY36QCGtcGo7y-SDddcCzA9P3uPaKK2DXPVQ1FmhVOpsyQWSlSlSgSjOwzuux), [10](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQGIey-iRWc80A2jOzngvjS-kejgrrEv9js65KqN4ZIvZOU4w_QIvQgV9sH7ed6s4_kGwGfbkC85gKlKpC1lCX4wwK4uEYa_Hvo6sd_tAbA7xnoGJUHY) " ;
