    mtr:llm_phenotype_driver " Gene-centric:FADS1/FADS2" ;
    mtr:llm_ratio_evidence " reaction where the ratio is shared through a pathway " ;
    mtr:llm_ratio_explanation " The ratio of 1,2-dilinoleoyl-GPC (containing linoleic acid) to 1-arachidonylglycerol (derived from arachidonic acid) reflects FADS enzyme activity in converting omega-6 fatty acids.[1](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQGAFEpTsgLt58wcihnc0YE-VdFbzgeFNEfRJ3ZAUigA00djZl5LzViILyhsgU_HemkBluYMaIiCibCFL5OqgYszHxpet5DqmLh1EZJqGGijzGzdudQ7Pcf6JZiWmybhvcpjFQNNoDBnbZCXnm_YsTyfNtKg), [5](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQEOTDpKToifqPmGWtt4yrBa5EPZqtE_c3JmQn50zKKQtozTHirTTnpcvttfcNET4mkX8OUUTgbwA496Txcm9tGamZuNdNHVUof7TtM9megpR8VLama_P5JPDMdUZpQUX2C-R3puygK-4EERUBADPZVfEMdoTuFS3Aj9MIEIkfNEWy-O7Q==), [6](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQHsM12F38nLnXshExeeR403lCNipqgMj6PAKY__2d_16JbFmg2k_8gOic_I9ReqKpRU0V3QRtSD061cTn4KwAJN8ZjCsHFJgqJVgEBgHKv449Tit92Jy6K1ubd1MkNGgy2rJT2J9NqB9wdP-eQ=) " ;
    mtr:max_pgain "7.52091675860392e+47"^^xsd:float .

mtr:GCST90200030_GCST90199899 a mtr:MetaboliteRatio ;
    rdfs:label "1,2-dilinoleoyl-gpc (18:2/18:2) to 1-(1-enyl-palmitoyl)-gpc (p-16:0)*" ;
    mtr:has_denominator chebi:73850 ;
    mtr:has_numerator chebi:42027 ;
    mtr:llm_gene_phenotype_relationship "  Reduced FADS1/FADS2 activity, indicated by the ratio, is associated with altered lipid profiles, including cholesterol levels, potentially contributing to hypercholesterolaemia and indirectly influencing hormone-sensitive conditions like follicular cysts.[1](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQFFmoWu4iqbqjRvlhtmwNzABWQVF7KAC3XWwgBf2Z4IdVpfIhRjCtHWRiiburq9Rg2G70a1JfBNrwQK1YDorOFayKKDj9OizpE-szUg78_CdpmS32_9jP8PHlCtqu1gUhnpU5kS), [9](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQEifO6HT1jcZ_4-84W5lVPya7QK5RM_B_2s74U7sfFVH7fTSbzwCeRiWgMVxolp07XQkN15vUMgJgfXPlBexjNqzScNXJaetzpkYJc2vWmSHBg1tcJLrkv3mAeXjf8ly1GiEqK8f2iammGSd9Nh7vPgT08pA7k=), [10](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQGoM5mwtS4dt5kblXc_bza7gmXmW3CDMVFOClrEen8g9tu-FaRSmcI8HVNrHes68oPq0x5wI5z5KBQNQPxOKsiCjp8FkktuFkik7svCaXUnPNVzJ5Ks7n6SuA==), [11](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQERVP2LpMpmh5actBQBxvXOfyH_A4BYRB3nASd20ivfgdwALKE7ILn36i84QimRjF1VT70f5zgbvfTMV8EnKKo6sO6eGnZTsiPel9jfO40gwQEyVJXSwjkaetgbuNqGvvmOZivf), [12](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQHQkGtd4CeJg8Y_e35tel69DWb65fNJ2a3L3w0OM1OWi7tFz29bZSUKohG3S3ZB59wymLuSMwLTZpF5BuG13d8nIE_NMEXOPJ49xd7cr-Byj4F2RyK_jqPFT1hjjEmRXTlAPgGvh81sTobzthEk6IcKqxHvdh-eF2NrInIn5h4KwShKUNnrzEGsig==)  " ;
    mtr:llm_phenotype_driver "  Gene-centric:FADS1 " ;
    mtr:llm_ratio_evidence "  reaction where the ratio is shared through a pathway  " ;
    mtr:llm_ratio_explanation "  This ratio may reflect the activity of FADS1/FADS2, where higher activity could lead to increased synthesis of polyunsaturated phospholipids relative to plasmalogens.  " ;
    mtr:max_pgain "1.675950802440074e+51"^^xsd:float .

mtr:GCST90200030_GCST90200010 a mtr:MetaboliteRatio ;
    rdfs:label "1,2-dilinoleoyl-gpc (18:2/18:2) to sphingomyelin (d18:1/22:1, d18:2/22:0, d16:1/24:1)*" ;
    mtr:has_denominator chebi:74533 ;
    mtr:has_numerator chebi:42027 ;
    mtr:llm_gene_phenotype_relationship " Genetic variants in FADS1/FADS2 are associated with altered fatty acid metabolism and inflammation, contributing to phenotypes like valvular heart disease, IBD, and type 2 diabetes by modulating the balance of pro-inflammatory and anti-inflammatory lipid mediators.[6](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQGjwFoQAq7Ay4W-qHfrE6BP1UanvS_657rgcuYxRZcm2rcvPlPScjip4F67PLNXtj7R8lL4MuwR_qtDwduPtf3ae1px_cXOb7hK1OnLv-gogUq3CVlu), [7](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQFNCowhebtIxphXNOSEoM4SeW_c1KTg6ffoPAhK_eOh6BPuSZtdxwNQdbc9-75ZO0ql-nugw0XLaZCl-YrBTVFmzsYKk77pXtDqYp0SkUUedZ4Z6Qs7cWY3f57w2qxpoOqe08EAodKZCFb-2rXdzUY6LcdhsEo=), [8](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQE8uGRO8my7IfRTwZKyN51uLoa6nC98qxtO_RgWgZ7d5sXKGGb75LExe0yBeFS0fsAgYTnrZ8yo44T-Y0R2TyVCdeRAH5o2rvVxx3CS5mxfj7zEv1WWwzkGH1bvR_1V5PXVxIa9BQBC1irQv2v0), [9](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQH8px6ZuPAQQeSJZYTtAJOnem6RDIxZCk75PU4MDglBVmrjP1vLzgAfR1465bOpR9KHGXkW6trFF-zpQBIaAgBieti2WXA_S6D4XLGbknFajfC2Nf-2QLq41_CqgZvCh9fnwcoYsMKE8zbq0GwYJH0yFgFnIPak_2sSHoZYM3I=) " ;
    mtr:llm_phenotype_driver " Gene-centric:FADS1/FADS2" ;
    mtr:llm_ratio_evidence " metabolites related through biology " ;
    mtr:llm_ratio_explanation " The ratio reflects FADS-mediated desaturation of fatty acids incorporated into complex lipids, indicating a balance between glycerophospholipid and sphingolipid pools. " ;
    mtr:max_pgain "3.013510783141055e+28"^^xsd:float .

mtr:GCST90200079_GCST90199742 a mtr:MetaboliteRatio ;
    rdfs:label "1-oleoyl-2-arachidonoyl-gpe (18:1/20:4)* to 1-linoleoyl-gpc (18:2)" ;
    mtr:has_denominator chebi:28733 ;
    mtr:has_numerator chebi:74975 ;
    mtr:llm_gene_phenotype_relationship " Genetic variation in FADS1/FADS2 alters polyunsaturated fatty acid (PUFA) metabolism, reflected by this ratio. This dysregulation of PUFA balance, critical for inflammation and lipid modulation, likely drives the associated risk for pure hypercholesterolaemia and other inflammatory or lipid-related disorders like cholelithiasis.[8](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQHtydnQFrCSc6GP4syCNebvHzuzcDEMbcsGwdDtaMma7mm4I3EoH8nDMWuRi4mVx46nKGxhWRWAhIhbadJcO4zyVGPMFQdAyKm4QnG6IeVTx6dKtNyM_eoa2A==), [9](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQGW_oboe7SemTBDlsSWT8zYtrQnuOomWjFvZs4I37KXjYMblmqZfpc81ATiqCSFuAGIDw__bEqxWTlaMUVes04cJeGn0WbHs5hvCMZcjq_nQogGN__R0K9WcFaNqP0jSI_hclToPVBbGLp0nbs=), [10](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQEVNTp_eUbp8KRXW4roZigtEwtY2P-DfFqzmiMzc9Cjhr2LMO3XG3ZrVCoVY73XedjNHL8w4zKCmOL18sSvkM_P6Wd4pbeG7zqQ5suOPIuQXZ5TF2E04AZAsuxyexNee77F9JNm-MceEGiGB4vCHydsYCqZ1WdsZowoUARl3HPBAb4THDn8BAgbzhZgAZnkC457) " ;
    mtr:llm_phenotype_driver " Gene-centric:FADS1/FADS2" ;
    mtr:llm_ratio_evidence " reaction where the ratio is shared through a pathway " ;
    mtr:llm_ratio_explanation " This ratio reflects FADS-mediated conversion of linoleic acid (18:2) precursors into arachidonic acid (20:4) products, indicating desaturase pathway efficiency.[1](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQGh2lceRNjM-1WfAXx6ygCi8k6TLYXzK7zeZiwiGRjtVyuNKPDLULUwCPY4DpjgX0nzEmUzVD94ibvrMSlMRSPYdOMJxkrGtLwTMy7bgL9m1TXCIBB_JL7upOiMEDWqlrKSW8uPRmkaIZQeK2Q=), [3](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQFqzPDcsSnXbMHXOoTDTdWDFtlX0mTTfQxv-yn8X5c4fK4xwCWlZlCXU7rgE0dR_BW18BBsbS60FQn6stak-iySsPI5c5cRla2lbJ_qkPLvdsm-ZSjjRvCaCnsWO6CTB5G7IQ_w) " ;
    mtr:max_pgain "227922091316.1684"^^xsd:float .

mtr:GCST90200243_GCST90200078 a mtr:MetaboliteRatio ;
    rdfs:label "hydroxypalmitoyl sphingomyelin (d18:1/16:0(oh))** to 1-myristoyl-2-arachidonoyl-gpc (14:0/20:4)*" ;
    mtr:has_denominator chebi:86102 ;
    mtr:llm_gene_phenotype_relationship " Genetic variants in FADS1/FADS2 alter the production of arachidonic acid and other pro-inflammatory lipids, influencing the risk for inflammatory and metabolic phenotypes like cholelithiasis, type 2 diabetes, and inflammatory bowel disease.[12](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQF8ZEaMFaAVokuh_xMemcITz1qZN2tR-F39otJEEAeGIkX7ajz1oniKpJNe83AQWJZ4pclXbepv9Oh5TXWFFZz3bP0C5cy_vSLJLT6Q3iRrkMwWdR1Gem91cgytIKeNYmiLtm-3aZrIvga6wyA=), [13](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQFolWwKxR5P4LIoK9jlt3LYkkhxd3WwIErbi2bAnDU6CK1TiSRNIRHSB_KAeuoUn7GVN83uLrdib3jajayG6CyVT2cqXlRKbBWl8KCBuG-ujASF_mKe89M5DKx3tDOEU-7OECnh), [14](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQHCu3CeNpc7hh4pTe_IFh6DcaHOYthdfWH-Ruza6qiip0M6frvTF5WBj98ArvmqYsz0aymCos4RXAkSui3zs600qwP3EuvzDUIRdIR2jjDZagPs7gZ_8b5uy9rLIjo7dwnQs2YVEW6rYrV_QBQ=), [15](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQFU_6ajFGNVadyBmhKeB6WOladJW6bO5wOef27DplDe7694db2kuOSWA76KndCKlm0XUON_sfVWeGOQ_V_PK9vz5t5vmYZ03tje36xKCTe79_7vDi6DZxe87Q==) " ;
    mtr:llm_phenotype_driver " Gene-centric:FADS1/FADS2" ;
    mtr:llm_ratio_evidence " metabolites not in a pathway but enzyme catalyzes one metabolite " ;
    mtr:llm_ratio_explanation " The ratio reflects the balance between sphingolipid pathways and the FADS-mediated synthesis of arachidonic acid-containing glycerophospholipids, a key process in inflammation.[10](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQFzDJQ8J24ehv7gmGi68GEFoPzgKHFJcPvnJi7eIkZxAqca5LLy6odIsr7rJH3lj6QWTY4psUD70rbcFQHeDW_f5fhaNVGKjX8vpzEpJbVv_yONvyhAQApGcfer4eC5o4YA_l19UKsX), [11](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQGNmXPnymDVCWkZ2ZAVQn_-2IDPZsr7n5tVQiWbO9Zdedx0FQ3Bh8gIZya90ns27XuzHL0Vu53_MbfVlvXv6AJR70E2eOUJRMbQbyMuymzX6X2N2eCPpXjZTbjPeSBAkZnMrbhfrQy-ItK8t1c=) " ;
    mtr:max_pgain "7.701542946118321e+26"^^xsd:float .

mtr:GCST90200330_GCST90200045 a mtr:MetaboliteRatio ;
    rdfs:label "1-palmitoyl-2-linoleoyl-gpc (16:0/18:2) to 1-stearoyl-2-arachidonoyl-gpe (18:0/20:4)" ;
    mtr:has_denominator chebi:78268 ;
    mtr:has_numerator chebi:73002 ;
    mtr:llm_gene_phenotype_relationship " Genetic variants in FADS1/FADS2 alter the expression and activity of these enzymes, influencing the balance of polyunsaturated fatty acids.[3](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQHAyOPYFxBQk8RRiJHeljoYPjqMyTRs91tgU3ygDLcZq_FTT8E4zxF0BPkSqscX-ZOC3Cf-p5h966kM6C41znejprZMH90XOYm0ZOl0EZyCOtA6AA3heNtmsx1lsg24qyUSNKwq), [7](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQGPhBHGPSU796d99Os8SrO1yPIuCphDkUTcfizWU7S5S2wQsAdufNDZqKHm71HOmaE1bKASzvT5DVZgoX5J15AXGgSNzsVQ4OH_FlVNhss2uZjWbjEi_9tpwxsvG636WpYYbg0VShohlkCuJ-2KKyo_KcMVAVroqSWGn8WWFIr8oxVyiz1o28j9xbwTPmoK) This altered ratio is associated with changes in lipid profiles, including cholesterol levels, which links to phenotypes like pure hypercholesterolemia and cholelithiasis.[8](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQFr5lkgq6r67Q52jNdgg4YfC87FMsDoTqGItdTFxyMHpb3hdyPAKLt1xJKG8-fpK6AMqfIb6qDeWiWpkiJ8ZhOc4tkrj7ogG9I2vO2nQ36zYJPD7RN1xw-DBk1C828Gvw7JHFynClYYqggEeMLVWVM1Cg1oeyQ=), [9](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQHlHSQ5UZwZ_iwJ1pHZ8RH6_t-6OO9TFsxXg32mJVNlPWTy_3AKrUPfXT5TN7LTx7WypTbA0YphaosjNxBhY2P83HSA5Y85sSQvLO2ZBa1vKFa2JmxphpZNNKWJlKFAwWKOMsgee0OJ4tlZ4ytijXfYPlV4gyWymXwq8wCEV90lI6JSMSPKxMP2B-4=), [10](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQFS9XVj5jGN3g-T9J6wgZAlcsjDcITLMVFhj76R56c1QFiczfxazqN3LIw7pw6j7XCtLDxHg2rK5sCssvgEU4688JuT6V_JD_HTfFhdzqtoebKHDbscrtkgWZx_L9VBBxyJyRUcR92P5FiegVQ=) " ;
    mtr:llm_phenotype_driver " Gene-centric:FADS1/FADS2" ;
    mtr:llm_ratio_evidence " metabolites not in a pathway but enzyme catalyzes one metabolite " ;
    mtr:llm_ratio_explanation " This ratio reflects the activity of FADS1/FADS2, which are crucial for synthesizing arachidonic acid (20:4), a key component of the denominator, from precursors like linoleic acid (18:2) found in the numerator. " ;
    mtr:max_pgain "1.618992404639805e+52"^^xsd:float .

mtr:GCST90200358_GCST90200459 a mtr:MetaboliteRatio ;
    rdfs:label "arachidonate (20:4n6) to margarate (17:0)" ;
    mtr:has_denominator chebi:32365 ;
    mtr:has_numerator chebi:15843 ;
    mtr:llm_gene_phenotype_relationship " Genetic variants in the FADS gene cluster influence delta-5 desaturase activity, altering the arachidonate/margarate ratio.[8](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQFaosDODHYCYrw6JMD2Vtv4tJP-H_JWizaJ-qN6858MpTsZ8NZENGk39j_6J2MQA2wSYnNAOAWvbh4bMFQkqDvsr6Si3eF-BsugdJ7HlbwSb-abKQiPFAkuT7xiYm8Wogy8jA0=), [9](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQGfxxf7u9Swsm20YJ8Yx_fSOAFbVz5A9s-guGv5i_tldghDe9SipYIUYoAzSify8v3XfsQOQtKL2kNOEV5qGUqpnFnA80DUocEBG5Tmqrc_t5q13WCUOkGi-ywNcRjFS-jG-iHVp3jaelK3FTxtmZVoL3vL1KmmQI8kY_W-8bwd8hbc1QBOMXBgulFzVhA=) This dysregulation of fatty acid metabolism is linked to an increased risk for inflammatory diseases, hypercholesterolemia, and benign neoplasms of the colon.[10](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQFfCJFMpOCfK7SokhKImq-GfZ_teu9mnfpdE02w0g2AyPe3kXK3FfOFO3a8Uj-CwO8uyCRVyAsWrqmpSOMX3swyfYJ0soSuNdtJv_YMADzRR7hj5OYoo2yEln99ORZ-e2rRniPhEz3UmUclSB5uvR3NZ4gm1xhUkcS5nA1c9Y8Rf99vwJPhIQ==) " ;
    mtr:llm_phenotype_driver " Gene-centric:FADS1" ;
    mtr:llm_ratio_evidence " reaction where the ratio is shared through a pathway " ;
    mtr:llm_ratio_explanation " This ratio reflects the activity of delta-5 desaturase (encoded by FADS1), where higher values indicate increased conversion of fatty acid precursors to arachidonate.[3](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQGKHbDR9UEdBWVXYVWgVt-d7otgD0ABEwZnA0X8DX8bjX0OqDUIKtPia7tii2rie-uhN8LmAzYSe3nK36SZNUGfjGVs1N2zXP9o9YVEycZWruYt7XJOcLsTL4j-OGAmc90Aibc_kg==), [7](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQF4SGPiYMTot5jbAn7ToImstqVin3wuIJ3K-HyZ_h0DT6KgINncUPiXyq8A3UoZTH1V8a9KyMQNY42g9JTxRG7YJqo17RTlSrEZuqTFtHD66kyJw5ySP6TvGKvDrM9GHKY7gGW-dQcyaKGQaRoWIoBStuw0VdxSPtYnblty-rPKAV9V_pdSTAGRyLZWYk-H5HgfZwYI612ivbf0DZMQgBSnH9CDRKM4BoZ8jbkoeO_Rjw0iMKq_wTptmjp32UF1DblHaSwxYrfzUCFSeoJa0UbjFqIZs3bFRhCrLrSywVGJrm3DVwOGhIR3pQmhw36Plh200Yaa0fDjfbVEQ8LO9PMII-z4InDtV7i2zJe8cBoXuLgVbb3I0ykqH-AFSbFE6TgV59ZpEvk2QlB0m7QnLMkTzuk8aE7Rtgyo4yB6Qh_IOvbwO_Lfylody5GvR-Mkbd6wF3_JyDr_xttoGQ4=) " ;
    mtr:max_pgain "5.292540016015836e+62"^^xsd:float .

