    mtr:llm_gene_phenotype_relationship " Genetic variants in the FADS cluster influence desaturase activity, altering the balance of polyunsaturated to saturated fatty acids.[1](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQE17SJveAXT64RikluSDdDA3mj7j8UDmUVLXC5ggUhwOtWxc41xoyiATKAlf5ameSCV24FQVkovsNc-5xvccGb3cuS233y5d63mIfH1FpOd6kD6WAO1JFoGf9tXYcZmxAYMx9U=), [7](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQFfEzuHYwogOvBX8R0R0AGhe7nojWzRVKDlGY9IcXw8kvVnzaJxIibphSJse-c1-sQbUZhJURm8j9zo6USrO2sNaWinXSlBCecE6dcj4L--x0svxRc=) This imbalance is linked to dyslipidemia, cholelithiasis, and type 2 diabetes, which are causally associated with this metabolic signature.[8](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQFHZDIzU8yOC_65yvbKSuAqemrp_4uWvaM9944T69lYpBJdiLmmN4idRG2e15YDGeikSsosT0Aa8mnscxPxU_uYlQChpk0vfLJZHZZpBrHN3QesRkAnKYf6d8C8r3ecRIcZpw==), [9](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQExEL_X3R72cZuA3gUi8x7Rdyk6KSlZTmMbE4AsX8Awkd9yYH2Ir3bqA-LLvBeJwP9RjteP0Yzi1eljz6GP-HZEhMhcmF6bzrY3eHmsBaTsjy8Y1NmK3H2VuuwwiLsui3GFtOL-lBaWpxfecy-JWZ8yzmKithcyd1eGqQ2yWfV8iXpc3DrwjSqOzAI=), [10](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQGMkhNxYvAEC4S1pUp6H-gvQ2ips9dNVKgD1RCLkbLiOlF_ctNbl4AFXpcYV1VyBoeFuwmgq6WRDUhRqj_ENXhAYoPVbD6Hv8CIIQx0Itx6qBUrLHaXLnyfBiIgSoh9EF6z4VZTwwyo1kSdpV3zphoHdvN1zDGbP5_y8Y7lwdsqh1jabg==), [11](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQFUL3SzNWmxw3qmGm0LR5I7VX7sLGCqu9HL2O4bpnSESrrxDYIBcAEumwub_Upvkmiu33JlYKoT-P9ROub0B6G3pgR8xHBRScJYXcrW2WHSmzID8M2LWuHOasFHVllj2Bvf_cMBaArNvng90Bxbjw8VZSv-mdMubW2nWfohwVXOp_n_WBHkR4BDYNm56xlTwh5X89k=) " ;
    mtr:llm_phenotype_driver " Gene-centric:FADS1" ;
    mtr:llm_ratio_evidence " reaction where the ratio is shared through a pathway " ;
    mtr:llm_ratio_explanation " The ratio of a phosphatidylcholine with polyunsaturated fatty acids to one with saturated fatty acids reflects the activity of FADS1/FADS2 enzymes.[1](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQE17SJveAXT64RikluSDdDA3mj7j8UDmUVLXC5ggUhwOtWxc41xoyiATKAlf5ameSCV24FQVkovsNc-5xvccGb3cuS233y5d63mIfH1FpOd6kD6WAO1JFoGf9tXYcZmxAYMx9U=), [6](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQE-X7Cvn6lTmcO_HX7m1Iw7SmyYDS8ExMQqvSGQki8PGp4a2EkhbvKoeZGBdr4JKzLwfM8HzwJkRYsWcWMHDP17ZoPioqL4GVmj3bAnhLEAk0Eq_7ygmE9VXXBgQKEPiWYZ9iZjw0AAoBo5nKk0SkvKCfQQYg==) " ;
    mtr:max_pgain "4.08516171183324e+98"^^xsd:float .

mtr:GCST90200040_GCST90199822 a mtr:MetaboliteRatio ;
    rdfs:label "sphingomyelin (d18:2/24:1, d18:1/24:2)* to 1-oleoyl-gpi (18:1)" ;
    mtr:has_denominator chebi:82753 ;
    mtr:llm_gene_phenotype_relationship " Variations in FADS1/FADS2 alter polyunsaturated fatty acid levels, impacting both lipid metabolism and inflammation.[7](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQE2wYGfGu1zP6BXCQfQiJc-seC3xbxLapiLrDOR40xf852Uh4Tc4D8lcCUDNaBhoLokC0IFJW5eZrLR61hN3su5wkExE7E_j7L_ImGY90Wx9SE9kGnjaXTuMkt0cVgFgFdOAi4B), [8](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQEDzdl3TCv8jBZ043mZqZX3yH91YaI97ogQsCeMjVZ4MJcybF6-6ALzHKFAB0BtpLLt6V6D46wQy0N56QyUKtu9WVRrD1lRiLems9YYDZKJ3kt1VNO1pnBF7y1VM_-yn3ZRgKIpZQzXbLQIPpUI) This systemic change is reflected in the sphingomyelin to GPI ratio and linked to phenotypes like hypercholesterolemia, dermatitis, and asthma.[3](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQGs6FM_RY0lR09szskgk06_eaEcPmvOJ2vaOT2aJvlxiCmXeEht5afOAWWMr9UHoKxXZC7f50roIo90UsSnkqKAEFkxSrSosX-U7CuKRkg-IQxYiM2a0RsBBQ==), [9](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQEfAsBF1mHLowfjhNRYHs1_A2ZoKTTP9HHIO-kzimEpe4ftNi3eTv9pvFRz0HuMH1Koq-TChDWmQvvEVEBHsXZN9OKrOP5e_2WymdiquD-0zDDfsy8dlUEBSUio6r_gXg4OdT5nnAm60xBeazVa_1LFM4n6d5k=) " ;
    mtr:llm_phenotype_driver " Gene-centric:FADS1/FADS2" ;
    mtr:llm_ratio_evidence " metabolites related through biology " ;
    mtr:llm_ratio_explanation " The ratio reflects FADS enzyme activity, balancing specific sphingomyelin species against a GPI-anchored lipid, indicating shifts in fatty acid flux between these pathways. " ;
    mtr:max_pgain "11286620.56925007"^^xsd:float .

mtr:GCST90200041_GCST90199742 a mtr:MetaboliteRatio ;
    rdfs:label "1-palmitoyl-2-stearoyl-gpc (16:0/18:0) to 1-linoleoyl-gpc (18:2)" ;
    mtr:has_denominator chebi:28733 ;
    mtr:has_numerator chebi:73000 ;
    mtr:llm_gene_phenotype_relationship " Reduced FADS1/FADS2 activity, indicated by a higher ratio of saturated to unsaturated fatty acids, is associated with altered blood lipid profiles, including cholesterol.[6](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQEZUWn-WNt5y8Yx52TU2guaCdPuSBrnGzluPqOmsn4TWFIuycD1CC71Rs0p2Sy7AcdmUUGV5koUzOw-dIIK6B0q8p9eS7oMq-C2FASV4DiK9oIdBVfSG70ezpkXLEyf43dLzNjiUNO_Bzsjx9Y=), [7](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQEVi-AtCAE9ZGR_sEPEFQu0B9lAEvs8orEgnU5-75bLbC6oQ3gY0q6Jv49UAAE3U83R9dnAUf9U7E2xqnrX0XnC_B1ZEMPEq_RKHcERi84kGpkT6-XKe6gAduQGjWRdbNkvhiU5) This dyslipidemia is a known risk factor for pure hypercholesterolaemia. " ;
    mtr:llm_phenotype_driver " Gene-centric:FADS1/FADS2" ;
    mtr:llm_ratio_evidence " reaction where the ratio is shared through a pathway " ;
    mtr:llm_ratio_explanation " This ratio compares a phosphatidylcholine with saturated fatty acids to a lysophosphatidylcholine with a polyunsaturated fatty acid, potentially reflecting FADS1/FADS2 desaturase activity.[2](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQFbpXVHzjourRNxOD5DJUKIAD-Y6C6PEvwV2_oyjtFM4DnBuGGRRduHAmoddl2I3flVLSZLhUzNdqTy1u53OKKvSNyZ1q-d4lajV4Wty7MAREMEZqrZe6n3uhMJP1Vq6wOrNqBs1dcgyBJJ6CCS9dWA__zLR0yQS9x_Zehfpx-HnhcBXfjdjCNrbuLLQbAoHT-hzAPDexenV03-SraRKpQ0J7Q9acPOFVMgVzh8c6-iwnO56ayPht2665XXfDSZwdPIi5SXii6c6ekECiDwgwyL8IHTBqezuznBuLX89sN24hJvh74JcFuVGBd5WZg3-zTRnRHXxK4fzuFWok_ajNiaFbfAeV0iv7rVmq7lG0vnOdqdSIcOFdyjk8ev), [5](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQFqO1TSfBTSAjaqwiGUwusBxS8JRX4drIjXHgCUTjkgZXpSN50nq1ein5m78aOwm_WyUhaeYNEJSN6g9u2XDrYU_fvXfOF-LrK-HF98c_TEJVsr_h8tCqcEd9t0FpotKgEk6u4lIFaGnKseAbw=) " ;
