    rdfs:label "sphingomyelin (d18:1/22:2, d18:2/22:1, d16:1/24:2)* to sphingomyelin (d17:2/16:0, d18:2/15:0)*" ;
    mtr:llm_gene_phenotype_relationship " Altered FADS1/FADS2 activity, indicated by the sphingomyelin ratio, impacts polyunsaturated fatty acid levels.[1](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQGXIsZByDDBpFIfrZIXS6MAuU3Xw_lz3NxeRAInvwcST1p5Nbvv9rl-fdg6_GqEPnAHSdEvLhhLnaCGo60KIavKdv-rx6vpwUzMxIe4YH6RFl7iIwxZpwwjBdHpR-Myu2embam_) This dysregulation of lipid metabolism is linked to an increased risk for cardiovascular diseases like coronary atherosclerosis and lipoprotein disorders, and also for cholelithiasis.[6](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQEOeEvUk9VDH5lDT5ZR7WSZNX2TUqGxURNZLxsKT0E-ZEWb15d87aEzotvEYZmHojt9MxHZk0WfCw-bDxTfBqhQGpY57hDEo85Do0Wdg_l-Q03sOEK9KiY7y7vZrXV-0R2fxEHbSl8oP33DTdU=), [2](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQGXkNOuw8WbDEmJe-puHnmJy1VkXoX0cXfKfJYACGKnKyxwlX0dsucKJf-uM3VgIQXxnZFIGT4tLkE2pRsr_oAwK8IE0qOHcDtJH_ZsxaCwGoDOTLmNDDFiWbkh15dHndx2L7EFO5ek-29YwmK8MlF18KUKObgAx_3tC9a-wJRU1E4dEac=), [7](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQHH6s8wWtjZ0n4oQwjA8D2YuJ5rTyPCCWDw_zPLm1srPz9OjQ3p60nlrXpA-i0d5pQeZRqy4Q1uCkuKNmnheQFgWS7fpSVs0sUP0z4cRQ4dlWF10gmxMOofa87-1a42p-Xy9w7mBtBHge2yIh-MxoFSaeebERx4ICB_4lIrsi8=), [8](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQGjyKN7lhwvx_j7Uu1Sff64ZvAADtT02q1TSh53umlom4m0mssSVJvCW-78X6yyx90B-StsKtDFLmKW_kL6DFe4fy3QA_B8sfYr6SMf-R8384YnoKcoidz6HuHcN4G_zrYVj1c5FsQfYu5RZXXHJpUsyiTbPFZsmYZls2vAIC14APLG_M6xwyElAbiipKDuTBI-cWk-JVxCE1GUg9Jic_4gzMCQza3hBP-1pjeXqrlWXKtQVVlTbnnh57X1oA9zAXLLLwjMpgtShw==) " ;
    mtr:llm_phenotype_driver " Gene-centric:FADS1/FADS2" ;
    mtr:llm_ratio_evidence " reaction where the ratio is shared through a pathway " ;
    mtr:llm_ratio_explanation " This ratio reflects the activity of FADS enzymes, comparing sphingomyelins with polyunsaturated fatty acids to those with saturated or odd-chain fatty acids. " ;
    mtr:max_pgain "7.314427656534411e+20"^^xsd:float .

